title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking soda, nutmeg and salt.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and cut up chicken and place in baking dish. Mix broth and melted butter with stuffing and place on top of chicken mixture. Bake 350 degrees until it bubbles. Chopped celery and onions cooked in broth can also be added to stuffing for additional flavor.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening, add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk and extract.
Add coconut, beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan (10-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and leave in pan.

title: almond stuffed peaches
directions: Peel and halve fresh peaches (or drain canned ones thoroughly).
Place cavity-side up in buttered baking dish. Combine almonds with sugar and orange rind.
Pile into peach cavities; sprinkle with a little more powdered sugar, then slowly pour sherry over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes (20 minutes for canned fruit), basting several times with sherry in bottom of dish.
Serve barely warm, garnished with slightly sweetened whipped cream flavored with 1/2 teaspoon almond extract. A magnificent dessert when fresh peaches are at their best. Yields 8 servings.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Cook celery and onion with 1 cup milk in the top of double boiler until tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove onion.
Melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper, add remaining milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling and cook 3 minutes.
Add celery and milk mixture.

title: beef and peppers stir-fry
directions: Cut beef steak into 1/8 to 1/4-inch strips.
Combine water, sherry and soy sauce.
Pour over beef and set aside.
Quickly stir-fry peppers in 1 tablespoon hot oil in large skillet or wok 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from skillet or wok.
Pour off and reserve marinade.
Quickly brown beef strips (1/2 at a time) in remaining hot oil.
Combine cornstarch with reserved marinade.
Add liquid and pepper to beef and cook, stirring, until sauce is thickened. Serve over cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving. Ingredients may be placed in blender for 20 seconds, if desired.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube.
Place half of bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube cream cheese and place over bread. Put remaining half of bread on top of cream cheese.
Mix eggs, maple syrup and milk together; pour on top of bread and cream cheese.
Make sure the bread is covered, but not floating.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes. Serve with more warm maple syrup.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole well.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Cover with a layer of oysters, salt and pepper and dots of butter.
Repeat until all oysters are used.
End with layer of cracker crumbs.
Beat eggs, milk and oyster liquid with lemon rind; pour over casserole and season to taste.
Dot with butter. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add remaining ingredients and mix together. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
(Double batch into 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Mix well. Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble the Ritz crackers and melt the margarine.
Mix crackers and margarine together and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 100 cocktail-size balls.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle the potato chips over chicken mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese over chips. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first 7 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender. Add ham. In another saucepan, melt the margarine; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in cheese until melted. Add to soup.

title: brisket
directions: Put brisket in pan. Pour liquid smoke over brisket, then cover with onion, garlic powder and the celery salt. Cover with foil and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Uncover. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Then drizzle with Lea & Perrins. Cover. Bake 1 hour per pound at 275°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box, making sheet cake. Let cake cool. Poke holes all over cake. Pour Coco Lopez over cake. Mix pineapple and condensed milk together and pour over cake. Cover with Cool Whip. Top with coconut and cherries. Cover cake and set in the refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: In saucepan put together sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir until clear.
Let simmer, cook to 310° on candy thermometer. Remove from
heat.
Add food coloring to tint.
Stir in cinnamon oil.
Pour on cookie sheet.
Cool and break apart.

title: birthday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Combine all ingredients except ginger ale in a gallon jar and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw to slush stage and add ginger ale.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Beat eggs well and add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° to 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce(california-style)
directions: Brown green peppers and onions.
Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer on very low heat 6 to 8 hours.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mash tamales and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: super slush
directions: Most Important:
Mix in exact order.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add sugar that has been dissolved in 5 cups of warm water.
Add pineapple juice.
Add 7 cups warm water.
Stir until well-blended.
Freeze.
Stir once while freezing.

title: easy day beef stew
directions: Mix all together and put in a large Dutch oven or casserole dish with cover.
Bake at 325° until
meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Do not brown meat first.

title: chicken creole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and next 3 ingredients. Saute until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients; cook 25 minutes.
Serve over rice; sprinkle with parsley.

title: zippy cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Melt cheese and add picante sauce.
Combine meat and cheese mixture.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: no fat dressing or dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in ovenproof dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, covered.
Stir.
Serve hot with Triscuits or corn chips.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, boiling water, sugar and cornstarch; boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Add strawberries to mixture and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with whole berries, if desired.
Let set in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and chill.

title: banana croquettes
directions: You will need 1 small paper bag.
Soak bananas in lemon juice a couple of minutes to keep from turning.
Cut bananas in half; using hands, cover bananas with salad dressing.
Put 1/2 of the nuts in bag.
Place 1/2 of the bananas in the bag and shake. Repeat with rest of peanuts and bananas.
Makes 12 single servings.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chile-cheese squares
directions: Spread half of the grated cheese over a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread the green chiles over the cheese and top with remaining cheese. Beat eggs with juice from chiles.
Pour over cheese mixture. Dust with paprika and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cut in squares and serve.

title: mustard and honey chicken(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: Broiler.
Baking Time: 7 minutes.

title: queque tres leches(three milk cake)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a greased and floured casserole dish.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Cover and blend on high speed until smooth. Serve immediately. Serves 1 (12 ounce portion).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Brown sausage, onions and mushroom stems.
Drain sausage and add cream cheese, stirring until melted.
Stuff mushrooms with sausage mixture.
Put in baking dish or on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.
Leftover stuffing can be sprinkled on top of mushrooms before baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Stir in flour; add milk gradually. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper, egg, cheese and broccoli.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: apple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars and beat in eggs.
Stir in sour cream, banana and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Gently stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon into greased bread pan and bake 1 hour.

title: super nacho dip
directions: Put beef and onions in frying pan.
Crumble and fry until brown; drain.
Add the refried beans.
Mix then spread in baking dish, sprinkle chopped chilies next.
Cover evenly with cheese and sprinkle taco sauce over it all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: hamburger-noodle bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, onions and green pepper, half at a time, until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Return drained noodles to kettle.
Stir in meat mixture, tomato soup, cheese, chili sauce, pimiento, salt, chili powder, pepper and 2 cups water; mix well.
Divide mixture between 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dishes.

title: ianniello spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in large pot
or frying pan.
Chop onion and pepper and saute with
meat until onion is translucent.
Drain grease. Add tomatoes
(chop
large
pieces) and tomato sauce. Bring
to a simmer on
medium
heat.
Add
spices
and
tomato paste.
Cover and simmer on
low
heat for 45 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine
squash,
onion, parsley and celery in saucepan with a little water and cook until tender.
Blend in blender, season with
salt
and
pepper to taste.
Add bacon, egg, milk and bread crumbs.
Mix
well, pour into 2-quart oblong casserole and bake at
for
20 minutes. Then top with grated cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: casserole of sweet potatoes and pears(yield: 10-12 servings)
directions: 1. Place the sweet potato slices tin a pot and add water to cover.
Heat to boiling.

title: zucchini, carrot, nut and raisin bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, zucchini and carrots.
Mix flour, powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves together.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend in vanilla, walnuts and raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: stromboli
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and peppers.
Cook, stirring often, 2 to 3 minutes or until soft. Remove from heat.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, bread crumbs, milk and egg together.
Form into balls.
Make sauce by mixing grape jelly, chili sauce and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Marinate overnight. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Makes 45 balls.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cinnamon candies to 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir to dissolve; add to jello.
Cool until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold. Chill to set.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cut potatoes in cubes.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: mrs. leavens white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients; alternate with milk.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with icing and cover with coconut.
Grease, flour and wax paper pans.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place sauerkraut on the bottom, then drained noodles.
Mix mustard, soup and mayonnaise with some sauerkraut juice so as to spread over top.
Sprinkle onion, then corned beef, then cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then uncover and let bake 15 minutes more to brown.

title: corn pone muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter, let cool. Sift meal,
flour,
baking powder and pepper into mixing bowl. Add butter
and
milk
to dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake until golden brown.
Heat greased muffin tin in oven for a few minutes before filling with batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: cold crab dip
directions: "Pick" crab meat.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Gently fold in crab meat.
Chill.
Spread on crackers, deli breads or fill mini cream puff shells.

title: chocolate marshmallows
directions: Melt butter; add chocolate.
Add white sugar and milk.
Cook until slightly thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla, marshmallows, wafers and walnuts.
Press in 8 x 8-inch pan which has been greased and slightly sprinkled with graham wafer crumbs.
Sprinkle more crumbs over top; chill.

title: hand dipped chocolates
directions: Mix all ingredients (will be stiff).
Chill overnight.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Line on a cookie sheet and chill overnight again.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Pour egg and milk mixture in bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Add melted butter.
Beat again and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake in 400° preheated oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In a large pan, saute onion and beef.
Add all other ingredients except corn.
Cook at least 1 1/2 hours; stir frequently.
Add corn; let simmer at least 15 minutes on low heat. If too thin, add some instant potato flakes and stir.
I usually cook this in the crock-pot and just let it keep cooking until ready to serve.
Add Tabasco, if desired.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Great on fresh mushrooms especially.

title: butter brickle dessert
directions: Mix together margarine, flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and pecans.
Spread thin in a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Crumble while hot; spread one half of mixture in a 9 by 13 inch pan.
Drizzle one half of jar of caramel sauce on top of mixture.
Cut ice cream in 1 inch slices, layer on crumbs.	Top with remaining crumbs and sauce.
Freeze.
Can also use butterscotch topping, if desired.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour. Drain mixture if water accumulates.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture; stir well.
Freeze in containers.
To serve, thaw in refrigerator.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork-curry pockets
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the sandwich spread and curry powder.
Stir in the finely chopped pork or chicken, carrot, coconut and green pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into pita halves or use bread to assemble into sandwiches.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dip tortillas in broth.
Line large pan with 6 tortillas.
Mix other ingredients and pour 1/2 mixture over tortillas.
Make a second layer of the same.
Cook 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (margarine).
Put 1 cup sugar and 1 cup Karo in pan on low heat to melt sugar.
Add peanut butter and melt.
Then add Rice Krispies; stir until coated.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: no-peek beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in Dutch oven with lid.
Cook for 2 hours at 325°.

title: mexican layered bean dip
directions: Spread bottom of a medium-size cookie sheet with the refried beans.
Next spread on the sour cream.
Then layer with rest of the ingredients.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop open; remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir gently to dissolve.
Add celery, apple and nuts, stirring gently.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to other ingredients and stir.
Pour into shallow decorative glass bowl and chill for several hours until firm.

title: goody bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, milk, 3 tablespoons butter and 2 teaspoons vanilla over hot water in double boiler.
Remove and cool.
Cream together 1 cup butter and sugar; add eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla, flour, soda, salt, oatmeal and coconut.
Press 2/3 of dough mixture into greased jelly roll pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over top.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add mushroom soup, eggs, sugar, onions and cheese to cooked squash.
Add 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over the remaining cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.

title: sausage mac
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water about 8 minutes or till just tender; drain.
Cook meat and onion until meat is browned; drain fat.
Add corn, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in cream cheese and milk.
Stir in macaroni and heat through.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Cook pork chops, brown on both sides and salt and pepper. Empty potatoes into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with sauce mix.
Stir in water, milk, margarine and pepper sauce.
Mix in beans. Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake until chops are tender, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt several times.
Add chopped walnuts.
In another bowl, beat egg and milk.
Stir into the dry mixture.
Put in pans.
Raise for 20 minutes; bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken ferninand
directions: Prepare crabmeat filling as follows:
In a food processor, chop green pepper, onion and bread.
Toss with crabmeats in a mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, lemon pepper, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Mix well and roll mixture into 4 equal balls.
Set aside.

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut; mix together.
Add powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls, dip in following mixture.
Melt chocolate chips and add paraffin wax.
Stick toothpicks in top of balls to dip into chocolate mixture.
Set on wax paper until cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each addition. Add extract, then the dry ingredients alternately with milk. Fold in coconut. Bake in greased and floured tube pan, starting in cold oven. Set thermostat at 350° when cake is put in oven. Bake 1 hour.

title: chocolate caramel chews
directions: Brush cookie sheet with 1 tablespoon melted oleo.
Place caramels, 3 tablespoons oleo and 2 tablespoons water in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Combine noodles and peanuts in bowl.
Pour caramel over noodles and peanuts.
Toss until coated.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons water.
Drizzle over caramel clusters.
Then refrigerate.

title: fried pizza
directions: Mix dough (flour, salt, shortening and water).
Let rest a few minutes.
Preheat oil to 365°.
Roll dough into rounds.
Put 1 tablespoon sauce and 1 tablespoon cheese in middle of circle of dough.
Fold dough over; seal edges.
Other toppings can be added to sauce and cheese.
Fry 3 minutes, turning once until pizzas are golden brown.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and margarine in a double boiler. Cook for 1/2 hour.
Cool and add vanilla.
Mix crumbs, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Pack in a greased pan.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Frost with melted butterscotch pieces.
These are hard to cut, but are very tasty...especially to the people who like butterscotch!!

title: harriet's caramel nut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and shortening.
Add the brown sugar and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating until creamy.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with the milk and vanilla until blended well.
Fold in the nuts.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until a cake tester inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Prepare pastry shell. Mound peaches in unbaked shell. In small bowl, mix sugar, eggs and flour until smooth. Pour over peaches. Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let set before serving. Serve with sweetened whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut stew beef into small pieces.
Fry in skillet until brown. Pour beef into saucepan with 2 cups of water.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours. Drain water. Add other ingredients.
Season to taste. Cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve hot with saltine crackers.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Bring berries to boil; add sugar and jello.
Let cool until it begins to thicken.
Whip milk and add to berry mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: white mountain strawberry pie
directions: Slice berries into pie shell.
Add frosting made as follows: Put egg white, sugar, water and corn syrup into double boiler. Place over boiling water and beat on high speed with mixer about 7 minutes or until thick.
Pour over berries.
Refrigerate until ready for use.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onions until tender.
Mix cheese and remaining ingredients together; combine with squash mixture.
Bake in a 2-quart greased dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach quickie
directions: Combine butter, flour, sugar, milk and cinnamon. Add peaches. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for about an hour or until done and brown on top.

title: rice pudding(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on top of stove on low heat until rice is done.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 8 minutes on High.
Stir well and continue cooking for 8 to 9 minutes on High, or until cabbage is tender-crisp.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes before serving. Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix well by hand the first 3 ingredients, forming into balls about 1-inch diameter.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Put 1 box of jello in a small bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir to dissolve jello.
Mix in 1 cup cold water.
Pour and chill in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish (or larger) for 35 minutes or until set.
Put 1 box of same flavor of jello into small bowl. Add 1 cup boiling water and stir to dissolve jello.
Mix in 1/2 cup chilled Milnot.
Pour onto first layer and chill (about 35 minutes) until molded.
Alternate the jello and Milnot mixture for each of the flavors.
Pour on last layers while still in refrigerator to prevent spilling.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Sauce:
Mix the two cans of soup, tomatoes with green chilies and chicken broth.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil together in just enough water to cover.
Make White Sauce.

title: janice browning's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water until done; debone chicken and return to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Prepare dumplings by mixing together the flour, egg, milk, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Knead thoroughly and roll out on a floured board.
Slice and place in boiling chicken broth.
Salt and pepper broth to taste.
Cook slowly, uncovered, for 10 minutes and covered for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add mayonnaise and butter. Dissolve the 2 teaspoons of soda in the cup of warm water.
Add to the mixture.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat well and bake in 350° oven until cake springs back.

title: twix bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer it with whole Club crackers.
For 5 minutes, boil the graham cracker crumbs, white and brown sugars, milk and margarine; pour over the whole crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Melt the peanut butter and chocolate chips; pour over the crackers.
Chill and cut.

title: honeybunn coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix with oil, eggs and sour cream.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan.
Pour in 1/2 batter.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle 1/2 over cake batter.
Swirl with knife.
Repeat with remaining batter and topping.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Glaze warm cake with powdered sugar mixed with vanilla and milk.

title: frozen bread dough rolls
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except	bread,	and do not cook puddings, then
cut 1 loaf bread into pieces and spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan .
Pour mixture over.
Put other loaf, cut up on top.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix frozen orange juice, lemonade, sugar and water together. Add maraschino cherries.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Very good for weddings.
Serves about 50 people.

title: berry pudding cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar thoroughly and add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in floured fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove tops, seeds and membranes.
Set upside-down to drain.
Place beef, onion, garlic and celery in a 2-quart microproof bowl.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 3 minutes.
Stir to crumble beef.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 4 tablespoons tomato sauce.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1
1/2	cups
boiling water (stir until dissolved).
Add strawberries and
half of Cool Whip. Cut cake in half. Break half of cake
in
small
pieces and put in a 13 1/2 x 8 3/4-inch pan.
Pour
half
of
mixture over cake bits. Break the other half of cake into bits.
Put these in pan over first layer and add
the
other
half
of
strawberry mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Top with remaining Cool Whip and serve.

title: avocado-grapefruit salad
directions: Peel grapefruit; section and seed over a bowl, reserving juice.
Peel and slice avocados.
Immediately combine juice, grapefruit sections and avocado slices in bowl; toss gently. Cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.
Drain and toss with lettuce in a serving bowl.
Combine olive oil and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly; shake vigorously.
Serve with salad.

title: baked beans(serves 175)
directions: Sort and soak beans in cold water 3 times as much water as beans (soak overnight).
Do not change water, just pour off until 1 to 2 inches of water is left over beans.
Bring beans to rolling boil and scoop off scum.
Set kettle in sink.
Put 2 tablespoons baking soda in beans.
Empty water and rinse beans several times in water.
Cover beans with room temperature water level with beans or 1/2-inch above beans.
Add 1 cup bacon grease.
Boil until half tender, about 1/2 hour and no more.
Scoop out juice and save.
Add molasses, salt, sugar and brown sugar.
Bake in 2 stainless steel pans or Pyrex bowl.
Bake at 350° until beans come to a boil.
Turn oven down to 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If cracking on top or too dry, add saved juice or a mixture of sugar and water.
Beans get thicker as they cool, so make an allowance for it.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select small, young beets.
Cook until tender.
Dip into cold water.
Peel off skins.
Mix ingredients.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour over beets and boil 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes at high speed with electric mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, ginger and nutmeg; add to pumpkin mixture and blend well.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, spreading evenly to corners.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake out into a towel sprinkled with 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and towel together, jelly roll fashion and let cool.

title: cheese pancakes
directions: Combine flour and eggs.
Add enough milk to make a thin batter (about half as thick as regular pancake mix).
Add sugar (as much as you want to make the batter sweet).
Fry pancakes on both sides.
Remove from pan; add cottage cheese in middle of pancake. Roll the pancake up.

title: strawberry yogurt popsicles
directions: Drain sweetened strawberries, reserve liquid. Place drained liquid in a saucepan and sprinkle with gelatin. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves. Mix strawberries, yogurt and gelatin mixture in a blender until smooth. Place cups on a tray or baking pan. Fill and cover with aluminum foil. Insert a stick by making a slit in foil. Freeze until firm.

title: hearty cheddar cheese chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in a Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan; blend in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir cheese sauce, pimento and hot sauce into vegetable mixture.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Do not boil.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix until crumbly and sprinkle on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening; beat for two minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until onion is yellow.
Blend in flour; stir in curry powder and soy sauce.
Stir in 1 cup water and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together until creamy, then pour on top of mixture pressed into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: fettucine crema
directions: Shred clean heads of cabbage and layer in crock with canning salt and dill.
Keep packing down the layers as you go, filling crock to desired level.
This will make its own juice to cover. Weight down with dinner plate with clean brick on top.
Cover with cloth and let ferment until it satisfies your own taste.
This will vary according to the temperature of the weather.
When ready, heat in large stainless steel or enamel pot and pack in jars.
You may wish to put in hot water bath to assure sealing.
I don't because I bring it to a boil and then pack it in jars.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; add mushroom soup and mix well.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 325°
for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and add Cheddar cheese.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; cool slightly.
While still warm, top with the frosting.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and syrup.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into pieces and wrap in wax paper.

title: chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken and apple; mix lightly. Combine rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Add mayonnaise to moisten.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Put it on a paper towel, then put it in a microwave for 12 seconds.
Then eat it!!!

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop vegetables and sprinkle salt over to let set overnight. Drain.
Mix remainder ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Boil 15 minutes and can.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Refrigerate.
Pour over any fruit or fruits.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured (or sprayed with Pam cooking spray).
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cake should look like isn't finished baking.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows (as desired) over top of cake.
Put back in oven.
Bake at 350° until marshmallows soften and puff up.
Remove from oven and let cool for 1 hour, then spread on icing.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: raised potato doughnuts
directions: Mix potatoes, liquid, shortening, salt and sugar.
Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Stir it into the potato mixture.
Stir in eggs and enough flour to make a dough easy to handle.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, greased side up (dough). Cover and let rise until doubled.
Roll out 3/4-inch deep on floured surface.
Cut with a floured cutter.
Let rise until doubled (approximately 1 hour).
Heat oil to 375° and fry until golden brown.
tags: liquid reserved from cooking the potatoes

title: chili quiche appetizers
directions: Sprinkle jalapenos, Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese in greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine baking mix, half and half, eggs and hot sauce in blender container.
Process at high speed for 15 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: marinated fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit, except strawberries, in large bowl.
Pour thawed orange juice over them.
Marinate overnight and top with fresh strawberries when you serve.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla, pineapple and flour which has been sifted with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Mix the second cup of sharp cheese with the stuffing and put on top of the cooked broccoli.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine and pour over the cheese and stuffing.
Bake for a few minutes, just until the cheese melts.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift soda and flour together.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks one at a time and add vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with the sour cream, using low speed on mixer.
Fold in egg whites carefully.
Pour into pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together. Chill for a few hours to let flavors blend.

title: cappuccino muffins
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients with fork.
Using whisk, mix liquids. Add liquids and chips to dry ingredients.
Stir about 2 minutes; will be lumpy.
Pour into greased muffin tins or cupcake papers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; add sauce, seasoning mix, water and beans.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 in baking dish and add a layer of cheese and a layer of Doritos.
Repeat, beans, cheese and Doritos.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: quick nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Work in shortening as for biscuits.
Then add egg and egg yolk (well beaten), milk and chopped nuts.
Beat thoroughly and turn into a buttered bread pan.
Let stand, then bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Put half of cornbread mixture on bottom of pan.
Add onion and layer of cheese.
Dice potato and add layer of potatoes, then all of the meat.
Add another layer of potatoes, onions and cheese. Top with remaining cornbread.
Bake until cornbread is golden brown.

title: church windows
directions: Mix together the chocolate chips and butter.
Combine colored marshmallows and pecans in a bowl.
Pour chocolate over marshmallows and mix.
Pour mixture out on waxed paper; shape into a log.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: picnic fried chicken
directions: Mix buttermilk and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in large, shallow dish; add chicken.
Cover and marinate for 1 hour, turning occasionally. Combine flour, salt, remaining pepper, monosodium glutamate and paprika.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Place on waxed paper; let stand for 30 minutes.

title: new orleans creamy praline
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans.
Use large kettle as mixture bubbles.
Stir and watch carefully.
Cook until it forms a rather hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and pecans; stir a few minutes off the stove.
Cool rapidly.
Drop on wax paper with tablespoon.
Yields approximately 40 small pralines.

title: john's birthday fudge
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, cook sweetened condensed milk and chocolate chips on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in cherries, nuts and liqueur.
Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: crispy eggs 'n bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove.
Pour off all but two tablespoons drippings.
Add croutons to reserved drippings and heat and stir until brown and crisp; remove from skillet. Slightly beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add to skillet.
Cook until nearly set, stirring.
Gently stir in crumbled bacon and croutons.
Cook until just set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In a pan combine white and brown sugar, water, salt, corn syrup and vanilla.
Cook at 260° to a hard ball stage.
Pour over popcorn in an open pan.
Roll up your sleeves.
Butter your hands liberally.
Form popcorn into balls.
Wrap individually in Saran Wrap.

title: energy cookies
directions: Place eggs in large bowl; beat thoroughly.
Add next 9 ingredients, mixing thoroughly after each one.
Stir in chocolate chips and M&M's.
Drop from ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet about 6 on a sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes. Yields 6 dozen monster size cookies.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and lemon juice.
Add fruit, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into large dish and freeze.

title: lemon and orange roughy fillets
directions: Combine
carrot,
couscous,
onion
salt,
lemon-pepper seasoning
and
nutmeg. Add water and stir, then divide into 4 individual
au
gratin
baking
dishes,
sprayed with nonstick coating.
Cut
fish
in
equal portions and place on top of couscous
mixture
in each dish, tucking under any thin edges. Cut lemon in 4 slices and place one slice on top of each piece of fish. Cover with foil and refrigerate 3 to 24 hours.

title: aunt hannah's cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until smooth. Add egg yolk and beat until light. Stir in flour. Add cream and vanilla, beating until you have a stiff but workable dough.
Divide dough into 35 portions. Roll each into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until just barely browned.

title: stuffed party mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms, pat dry, remove stems. Place caps on a greased baking sheet.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix; add milk and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add strawberries, coconut and nuts.

title: the wurst potato salad
directions: Place in steamer and steam 20 to 25 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, milk and softened cream cheese.
Stir and keep warm until mixture is smooth.
Put hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes and top with shredded cheese of choice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: buttermilk cornbread(reduced-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray baking pan with no-stick spray.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in greased tube pan.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat by hand.
Sift flour and cocoa; add to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven for 10 minutes.
Cool; ice with chocolate fudge icing.
Add nuts to icing.
Can be frozen.

title: creamy cucumber dressing
directions: Blend cucumber, garlic, water and mint leaves until smooth. Add other ingredients and blend.
Chill before serving.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Take tomato juice.
Let stand in warm place 4 or 5 days until it really sours.
Skim off top and part of water from top.
Use remaining juice and add sugar and spice to taste, 1 onion (ground real fine) and salt.
No vinegar is used.
Boil slowly until thick. Pour in pint jars and turn upside down 24 hours to seal.

title: banana mandarin pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle brand milk until smooth.
Stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice and vanilla.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Put soy sauce, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in 1 cup measuring cup and add water to make 1 cup.
Put this mixture into large bowl with the rest of ingredients, except beef.
Mix together.
Add beef and refrigerate at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally to marinate . Put on skewers and grill or broil to desired doneness.

title: good green bean
directions: Combine all in pan and bring to a hard boil. Turn heat down and simmer for 1 hour or until almost all liquid is gone. This taste like fresh green beans. Cooking for a long time makes the difference.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix
for
5 minutes. Butter Bundt pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Put into 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings (serving size:
one 1 1/2-inch slice).
Half of recipe yields 3-serving loaf; 1/3 of recipe yields 2-serving loaf.

title: peach yogurt pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with yogurt and vanilla, beating well after each addition.

title: speedy caramel frosting *
directions: Melt margarine, blend in brown sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring.
Add milk; cook to boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in 10x sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well. (Mixture may be thinned with a small amount of milk or thickened with more 10x sugar.)

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a cool place.
To use, put 1/3 cup mix in a mug.
Dissolve in a little cold water.
Add boiling water and stir.
Add mini marshmallows if desired.
To make cocoa for a crowd, add 8 cups water to entire mix.

title: tomato relish
directions: Grate peppers and onions together and let drain in refrigerator overnight. Scald and peel tomatoes.
Cut into quarters. Cook tomatoes 40 minutes in kettle. Add all other ingredients and cook 1 hour or until mixture thickens.
Pour into sterilized jars or freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar with an electric mixer. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff. Blend in last flour by hand. Do not chill dough. Divide dough into 2 balls.
On floured surface, roll each ball in a circle about 12-inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick.
Dip cookie cutters in flour before each use. Bake cookies on ungreased cookie sheets on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Decorate as desired.

title: cheesy grits
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Gradually stir in grits.
Reduce to low heat.
Cook five minutes or until thick.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: beef stew
directions: In large pan, brown meat in oil.
Add 2 cups water and next 8 ingredients.
Cover, simmer for 1 hour.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 40 minutes.

title: meat kabobs
directions: Place pork and turkey pieces in a glass bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over pork and turkey pieces.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring, 2 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar together; add pumpkin, egg and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef roll
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dried beef. Lay out 6 slices of dried beef (3 across and 2 down). Spread with layer of cream cheese mixture, beginning with shortest side. Roll as for jelly roll. Continue procedure until all ingredients are used. Chill overnight. Slice into 1/4-inch slices.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into bite-sized pieces and marinate in salt and Accent for 1/2 hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of a large salad bowl; sprinkle with a little salt, pepper and sugar.
Spoon peas evenly over the lettuce.
Add egg slices and bacon over the peas.
Top with shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and paprika. Spread mayonnaise mixture over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill salad in the refrigerator up to 24 hours. Garnish top of salad with sliced green onion.
Toss before serving.

title: heart smart rich mocha cocoa
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, cook milk and cinnamon stick about 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine cocoa, sugar and coffee powder.
With a whisk, blend mixture into milk; add vanilla.
Cook about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove and discard cinnamon stick.
Pour into mug.
Makes 1 serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in parsley and mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix milk with biscuit mix.
Roll 1/4-inch and line in cake pan.
Pour hamburger mix over dough.
If any dough left, roll thin and cover meat.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Brown onion and beef in oil.
Add corn, soup and seasonings.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, place two layers of spaghetti, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezable.
Warm up leftovers in microwave. Makes 8 servings.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Cook and stir onion in 2 tablespoons margarine in 1-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Sprinkle over corn.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baked squash
directions: There are no specific proportions for this dish, so you may make as large or small a casserole as you wish.
It's wonderful with fresh summer vegetables.

title: mints
directions: Cut sugar into cream cheese.
Add oil and color (if desired). Hand knead until smooth.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed. Pick cake with fork all over while cake is hot. Pour pineapple and juice over cake. Blend pudding, milk and cream cheese together. Spread over cake. Put Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle with coconut and refrigerate.

title: kraft oven-tender chicken recipe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes. Cooking time:
1 hour.

title: easy banana cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk as per package directions; set aside to set up.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and remove centers from peppers.
Place upright in greased baking dish.
Mix the meat loaf seasoning mix according to package directions with ground meat.
Stuff meat mixture into peppers; cover and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over peppers and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Mix Jell-O and let set until beginning to jell.
Grind orange and cranberries.
Cover with sugar and let stand until dissolved, then add to Jell-O and add nuts.

title: date bread
directions: Boil the water.
Add dates and soak.
Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add egg, vanilla and nuts.
Add date mixture.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach & sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and sausage together; drain. Fold in mushrooms, cheese, spinach and seasoning salt.
Place in greased casserole; sprinkle with extra cheese.
Cook covered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: devilish shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp and drain.
Season with salt and peppers; set aside.
Simmer celery, bell pepper, onions and garlic in oleo until tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(Don't overcook.)
Use butter sauce for dipping shrimp.
Also makes a great finger party food.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt and let stand for 3 hours. Drain off salt water brine.
Bring sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar to boiling point.
Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil (about 2 minutes). Place in pint jars and seal immediately.
Makes approximately 7 pints.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add cheese and milk. Once cheese has melted, add picante sauce, chopped pepper, onion and jalapenos. Add or omit jalapenos according to taste.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large shallow pan.
Place frozen T-bone steaks in marinade, cover with foil and refrigerate for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove from marinade and cook on grill.

title: cheeseburger delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Make small patties.
Place slice of Mozzarella cheese between 2 patties. Fold together.
Grill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add cake mix, jello and instant pudding mix together.
Add eggs and oil; mix well.
Fold in strawberries.
Add 7-Up drink last.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour into three 9-inch pans, greased and floured.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% bran.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk and bran.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to rest.
Store in refrigerator, tightly covered. Add raisins or dates when baked. Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits, marshmallows and nuts. Beat egg until light and foamy. Add sugar gradually.
Blend in light cream and lemon juice.
Place egg mixture in a saucepan and cook over low heat until the sauce is smooth and thickened, stirring constantly. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over combined fruit and mix lightly.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: meat spinach filling
directions: Melt butter in skillet
and add meat.
Cook until brown and drain any grease.
Return to
heat and add dry spinach and saute for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Proceed to fill dough as stated in recipe.

title: veal chops with artichokes
directions: Sprinkle chops with garlic powder, pepper and cook in a large skillet in oil, 3 to 4 minutes until brown on each side.
Remove from skillet and drain well.
Add water in skillet and rest of ingredients.
Place chops in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish that has been coated with cooking oil.
Top with tomato mixture and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: creamy pineapple-lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple well, reserve syrup.
Add 1/2 cup syrup to gelatin.
Chill until very thick (spoon drawn through gelatin leaves a definite impression, takes about 1 1/2 hours).
Fold in pineapple, cheese, cream, cherries and peaches.
Chill.

title: nut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add Crisco, milk and 2 eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add remaining 2 eggs and beat for 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Put in well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: jelly roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil or wax paper; grease.
Beat eggs about 5 minutes until very thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in granulated sugar.
On low speed, blend in water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Loosen cake from edges of pan.
Invert on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Carefully remove paper or foil. Trim off stiff edges if necessary.
While hot, roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool on wire rack.
Unroll cake; remove towel.
Beat jelly slightly with fork to soften.
Spread over cake.
Roll up. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
You may use different fillings, all are very good.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in blender. Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: fruit salad
directions: This recipe is an English translation of an Italian recipe from an Italian regional cookbook.
It was submitted by Marie (Coia) Levi for your enjoyment.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix the butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the flour and salt, then mix into butter mixture, along with chopped walnuts.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the 6 tablespoons butter over low heat in a cake pan. Stir in the 1/2 cup brown sugar until smooth.
Remove from heat and sprinkle the nuts evenly into the pan.
Place apples in the pan in a circular pattern, covering bottom of the pan completely. Set aside.

title: green pea salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place the ingredients in layers in the order listed.
Seal with mayonnaise.
Top with grated sharp cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss right before you serve.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice and water in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer pork chops on rice; spread onion and garlic on top of pork chops. Spread soup over top of onion.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top; drizzle oleo.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: onion souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with an electric mixer. Put into a casserole or souffl dish and bake at 375° for about 35 minutes until lightly browned on top. Serve with meat or vegetable dish.

title: campfire stew
directions: Fry meat and onion until lightly brown.
Drain off grease and add undiluted soup.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Water can be added.

title: savory farmhouse bread pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Generously butter a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Combine the cornbread and biscuits. In another bowl, beat together the broth, milk, and eggs. Pour over the bread and mix well.
Stir in the vegetables and chicken mixing well. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 55 to 60 minutes until set and lightly browned on top.
Serve with Buttermilk Sauce.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Cut hot dogs into 8 pieces each. Brown in large pan. Add water, tomato sauce, thyme, wheat germ and pepper; let bubble. Lower heat and let simmer. If water goes down, add a little more. Serve over cooked rice. Corn as a side dish can be mixed in with the stew.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 pan as directed on box.
As soon as you remove it from the oven, take a fork and make slots every inch on the cake.
Pour pina colada mix over entire cake and follow with the condensed milk.
Put in the refrigerator to cool.
Later, spread the Cool Whip over the cake and then sprinkle coconut over it.
Keep refrigerated in pan.
This is wonderful!!

title: french fried hot dogs
directions: Mix together milk and egg. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together in long shallow dish.
Dip hot dogs into batter, then roll in bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes. Deep fry and serve.

title: "chili" california style
directions: Spray deep skillet with Pam.
Brown ground turkey and add chili mix (set aside).
In blender, mix tomato sauce, tomato paste and tomato soup (set aside).
Cut up all of the vegetables (set aside).
In a large saucepan (6-quart capacity), add ground turkey.
Slowly pour in the liquids.
Stir well.
Add all of the finely cut vegetables.
Stir.
Add the kidney beans, juice and all! Stir once more and add 1 cup of water (purified).
Add garlic and cook for 2 hours on medium, stirring often.
Serve with a salad and Italian bread.
Serves 6 hungry people.

title: watergate cake
directions: Blend all ingredients into large mixing bowl, then beat two minutes at medium speed. Bake in three 9 inch greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix soup and 1 can of water together in a baking dish.
Add chicken and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and then add 1/4 cup finely chopped onion. Mix well.
Serve with crackers, etc.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour and milk, then add corn.
Pour into a dish that has been well coated with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least two hours before serving.
Makes two pies.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in an airtight container.
To prepare one serving, add 3 tablespoons mix to 6 ounce cup hot water.
Yields 3 cups dry mix.
Put in jars as gifts for Christmas or just because.

title: crystal pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in brine. Keep covered completely with brine or they will mold. Let stand 2 weeks. Take out of brine; wash and cut in thin slices. Put a piece of alum or 1 teaspoon powdered in enough water to cover the slices. Let stand overnight. Drain and wash. In a bag, tie cinnamon and whole cloves. Add to vinegar and sugar. Bring to boil and pour over slices. Repeat 3 mornings. On 4th morning, put slices in jars and pour the hot vinegar solution over them; seal. Not necessary, but I usually process in hot bath for 5 minutes to insure sealing.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy pan.
Bring to a boil on high heat; turn down and let boil 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour into sterilized jars; seal at once.
Makes 4 pints.

title: crock-pot hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef into pot.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Stir in water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.
Add celery and carrots.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Add cooked macaroni and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; store in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.
Mix salad again completely before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, and sugars together thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and stir into first mixture, mixing well.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and chiles.
Heat until boiling, stirring often.
Dip tortillas in medium hot grease. Drain on paper towels.
Put small amount of meat mixture on tortillas and roll up.
Place in a greased oblong baking dish. When filled, pour sauce mixture over enchiladas.
Cover with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: jim's sauerbraten
directions: Two to four days before serving, combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Place meat in this mixture and let stand for 2 to 4 days, covered, in refrigerator, turning each day.
At the end of marinating, remove meat and dry on paper toweling.
Brown well on all sides in shortening in Dutch oven.
Strain marinade and add to meat.
Also add as much of the onions as you can separate.
Add mustard seed, cloves and peppercorns.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until the meat is tender.
Remove meat to heated platter.

title: potato chips cookies
directions: Mix everything together
in
the order they are listed. Roll into small balls,
press down lightly with fork.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove
from
cookie
sheet,
let cool a few seconds and dust with powdered sugar if you like.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.
Very rich
and
you will be unable to decide what is in them
unless,
of
course,
you
know.
Most people think they are made with almonds!

title: cheddar chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the chicken, 1 cup of cheese, soup, milk, salt and pepper. Drain spaghetti, add to the chicken mixture and toss to coat. Transfer to a greased 13x9 baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until heated through.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: This salad does not keep very well
overnight as lettuce wilts.

title: fern weinhold's salad dressing
directions: Fry chopped bacon slowly, until brown.
Mix sugar with salt and cornstarch.
Add beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Add to bacon and fat.
Cook to desired thickness.
Chop a small onion in dressing before placing on greens.
Good on leaf lettuce.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Grate carrots, add salt, brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon and sufficient water to keep carrots from sticking to
1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy garbage
directions: Break up pretzels and mix with all dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate.
Blend chocolate into dry mixture and press together firmly on a large cookie sheet or two small sheets.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice package of rolls in half.
Place bottom layer back in pan.
Spread ham over bottom layer; sprinkle with cheese.
Place top of rolls in pan.
Mix other ingredients together and spread on top.
Let soak in 10 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into sections.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and shortening well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old-world stuffed pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil on both sides; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Alternate the pork chops and stuffing lengthwise in a greased 3-quart or 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or boil in water for 20 minutes or until soft.
Cool, peel and mash until smooth.
Add margarine or butter.
In large bowl, beat eggs with sugar, spices and flour.
Add mashed potatoes and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Put into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours until done.
Can be served with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add to beaten egg yolks.
Add rhubarb and mix all together.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use 1 greased tube pan or divide into smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Smaller cakes take slightly less time.)

title: fried oreos
directions: Make up mix according to package, but make mix a little thinner like pancake batter. Dip Oreos in batter and fry in hot grease. Drain and dust with confectioners sugar. One mix does a large bag of Oreos.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onions, chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortillas(crepe type)
directions: Combine flour, corn meal and salt in mixing bowl.
Add milk, egg and melted butter; beat until smooth.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake skillets of cornbread.
Crumble into large mixing bowl. Add chopped onion and sage and mix well.
Add broth from turkey or chicken until the mixture is well soaked.
Put in baking dish. Pour more broth over mixture.
(It should be enough to puddle in spots.)
Bake at 350° until brown.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: cowley k-bobs
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch cubes and place in mixing bowl (2 to 3 pounds).

title: honey-que barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
I like to add garlic powder.
This is good on chicken, pork or hamburgers.

title: easter egg bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add to milk mixture 2 eggs slightly beaten and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough. Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in a large greased bowl, turn to coat.
Cover and let rise, about 1 hour, until doubled.
Punch down; cover and let rise again until almost doubled, about 30 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Form each part into a 36-inch rope.
On a greased baking sheet, twist 2 of the ropes into a loosely braided ring, leaving space for 6 eggs.
Insert 6 eggs into spaces.
Repeat with remaining 2 ropes of dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with colored sprinkles.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: crab dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add crab and soup.
Mix well.
Serve in chafing dish with crackers.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Beat eggs with the sugar. Add butter, mustard, a little pepper and lastly the vinegar. Cook like a soft custard. Add 1/2 cup sweet milk.

title: taco dip
directions: Warm beans to soften.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer the rest of the ingredients:
onion, guacamole dip, sour cream mixed with 1/4 picante sauce, chilies, cheese, olives and remaining picante.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: 6 layer cookies
directions: Layer all 6 ingredients in order given, starting with butter. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill; cut into pieces before serving.

title: onion dip
directions: Blend onion soup mix with sour cream.
Chill before serving.

title: apple mystery dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Pour canned pineapple and juice into dish.
Toss together the apples, 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Place on top of the pineapple. Sprinkle fruit layers with dry cake mix.
Top with melted butter, 1/4 cup sugar and chopped pecans.
Bake 20 minutes, then cut with a knife to allow juice to rise to the top.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: easy 7 minute frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, mix syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cook until mixture comes to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Gradually add this to the egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until it's the right consistency to spread.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine and blend cream cheese and milk.
Add crab meat (which has been picked over and cleaned), onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Blend well by hand or in a blender.
Spoon mixture into oven proof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or party rye.
Can be made a day ahead and heated before serving.

title: noodles mexicali
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain.
Meanwhile in large skillet brown beef, onion, celery and garlic.
Drain excess fat.
Add corn and mushrooms.
Heat 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese. Mix well.
Add cooked noodles.
Mix.
Transfer to 3-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and cheese has melted.
Yields 8 to 9 servings.

title: hornet nest cake
directions: Prepare pudding and cool slightly.
Add cake mix.
Stir well. Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Cover with butterscotch chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange with peel.
Add nuts and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let cook until consistency of egg white.
Stir in cranberries, orange and nut mixture.
Pour in mold and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in dishpan or very large bowl, all ingredients in order given.
Drop by ice cream scoop on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
No more than 6 cookies per sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° for 10 minutes, then increase to 350° and cook for 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and rice; pour in a casserole dish.
Roll chicken breast in butter and place on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for an hour and half to two hours.

title: crab soup
directions: Put water in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Place carrots, onions, celery, butter, seafood seasoning and Worcestershire sauce in water and return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook about 20 minutes, until potatoes are done, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cartilage from crabmeat and add to soup when ready to serve.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: coke salad or dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries and bring their juice to a boil. Add jello and mix well.
Add fruit, cream cheese and nuts; mix well.
Add Cokes last and mix.
Can be served as dessert topped with whipped topping, or as salad on bed of lettuce.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: good and easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add rolled oats, raisins or candied fruit or chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Add in order:
corn oil, eggs and milk.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheets, about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar and continue creaming. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add flavoring.
Put into tube pan and bake 1 3/4 hours at 325°.

title: barbecue baste for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and run on high speed for 1 minute.
Put chicken on grill skin down with medium heat for 3 - 4 minutes.
Turn chicken and paint baste on browned side.
Keep repeating procedure until fully cooked.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk until fairly thick, then add peanut butter and blend until thickened like pie filling.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for a few hours until jelled, then serve cold.

title: baked corn favorite
directions: Combine corn, soft butter, garlic salt, cornbread mix and beaten eggs. Stir until well blended. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with shredded cheese. Bake for 10 minutes or until center is set.
Recipe can be cut in half or enlarged.
Baking time should then be adjusted.

title: candy from sue
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips in pan.
When all are melted, remove and stir in vanilla, marshmallows and cornflakes.
Mix until well coated and drop on wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: guacamole from mexico
directions: Chop up the green onion.
Peel and chop the tomato.
Peel the avocados, cut in half and take out the seeds.
Mix all the ingredients together (either mash them up with a fork or use an electric blender).

title: brownie oat cookies(fat free)
directions: Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine oats, flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened (dough will be very thick).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet. Remove; cool on wire rack.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute green onions, peppers and celery in butter.
Add other ingredients, mix thoroughly and place in casserole dish.
Bake until hot or until bubbly.

title: low-fat spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large skillet, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, brown meat and onion.
When meat is done, add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat approximately 15 minutes.
Serve over pasta. Makes 8 servings; each serving 166 calories and 2 grams of fat.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, bouillon, salt, thyme, rosemary, garlic and pepper.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat; add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hello dolly bars(mom's favorite)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: dutch kale and potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until soft.
Drain water.
Add kale with juice, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Mash with masher or blender.
Leave all in pan and place kielbasa on top of mixture. Return to heat and steam until kielbasa is hot.
Watch that potatoes don't burn.
Serve with spicy mustard.

title: nutty buddy pies
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until blended.
Mix in sugar and peanut butter until blended, then fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mixture into all three graham cracker crust. Drizzle each with chocolate syrup, and a sprinkle of peanuts. Cover and freeze for about 2 to 3 hours.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before serving.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine meat, onion, rice, water, salt and pepper and make into small balls.
Place in baking dish.
Heat to boiling the soup, water and chili powder.
Pour over meatballs and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or cover and bake in 350° oven until done, probably 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
Combine margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over the sifted ingredients.
Stir well.
Do not use mixer.
Add buttermilk, salt, slightly beaten eggs, soda and vanilla to other ingredients.
Mix and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake *
directions: Beat up eggs.
Add brown sugar and flour.
Add the other ingredients.
Add the orange juice a little at a time to keep it soft enough to mix well.
Cook in round pan with spout.
Grease pan good.
Put wax paper in the pan and grease the paper good. Wrap good and put in pressure cooker.
Steam for 20 minutes, then cook for 50 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.
Uncover and put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Brown chops.
Place on top of potatoes and bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook corn syrup, water and sugar for 6 minutes in microwave on High in uncovered dish.
Meanwhile butter cookie sheets.
Remove from oven and stir.
Add peanuts.
Return to microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add butter.
Cook another 8 to 10 minutes on High, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla to mixture, it will bubble up.
Spread into cookie sheet.
When cold break into pieces.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the green pepper and put into a saucepan.
Cook this mixture until it thickens. Next, place sauce in crock-pot over meatballs. Cook for at least 3 hours. Then, add chopped raw green peppers and serve.

title: spicy flavored rice
directions: Brown turkey
sausage
in
saucepan.
Add onion, diced. Let cook until	brown.	Add rice, black pepper and water.
Let cook until done.
Serves 4.

title: rocky mountain pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour; stir and add remaining ingredients.
Put mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
