directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add oil and sugar.
In another bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine the egg mixture and the dry ingredients.
Add the strawberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Place mushrooms, onion and tomatoes in Pam sprayed pan. Sprinkle with other ingredients. Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes. Serve at once.

title: cherry delight
directions: Place half of torn cake pieces in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Spread pie filling over cake pieces.
Spread remainder of cake pieces.
Beat instant pudding mix with the milk.
Add sour cream and continue beating until well blended.
Spread pudding mixture over cake.
Allow to set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture on bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over mixture.
Beat 3 eggs until well mixed.
Add corn syrup, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, alternately with apples.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Do not mix vegetables with dressing until 2 hours before serving.

title: lazy stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute meat and onion soup in a skillet until browned.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add rice to meat mixture.
Put sliced cabbage into large baking pan or casserole.
Spread ground beef mixture over cabbage.
Mix water and soup; pour over meat.
Cover an bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lynn's fall muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins to prepare them first.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and pumpkin; beat thoroughly.
Take approximately one-half of this mixture and mix with the Quick Quaker oats.
Let this stand.
Add all dry ingredients to the original mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Add oat mixture, vanilla, grated carrots and nuts.
Add raisins, if desired.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full and sprinkle tops with brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in fat until lightly browned.
On cutting board, thinly slice garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and mash thoroughly to pulp.
Add to beef with onion, green pepper and chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tomatoes. Combine rice and kidney beans in 2-quart casserole.
Add hot beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into strips and brown with chopped onions in oil. Add additional ingredients except sour cream and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and add sour cream.
Cook 30 minutes longer and serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: kris kringle cookies
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in large pan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Mix in cereal.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let harden.

title: lisa's favorite peanut butter and chocolate cookies
directions: Beat the butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
In a separate bowl, sift together cocoa, flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold into butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and chips.
Chill at least 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop batter onto baking sheets in teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts. Place chicken, vegetables and broth in crockpot. Cook on high for 2 hours. Serve with Cornbread.

title: orange pudding cream(filling for bisquettrolle)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups cold water, bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from stove.
Add dissolved jello and stir.
Keep in refrigerator to cool, then beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in jar and shake.

title: swiss steak in sour cream
directions: Dredge steak with flour and seasonings.
Brown on both sides in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover pan closely and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican flan
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are well blended.
Add granulated sugar and salt.
Beat in evaporated milk and vanilla. Sprinkle brown sugar into bottom of loaf pan.
Gently pour custard mixture over brown sugar.
Place loaf pan in shallow baking pan containing hot water.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, run knife around edge of pan and turn out onto small platter.

title: pennsylvania pepper steak
directions: Cut thick cubes of meat into thin slices.
In large skillet, brown meat lightly.
Set aside.
Slice peppers into long, thin slices.
Add to meat with tomato sauce and water.
Stir and simmer.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Simmer one hour, stirring occasionally.
When meat mixture is tender, boil water for noodles.
Cook according to directions.
Serve meat mixture over egg noodles.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Boil mixture until it forms a soft ball.
Pour over hot prune cake without beating.
(I like to use a low Pyrex dish for baking my cake, so as to leave cake in pan until ready to cut into blocks for serving.)

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat together eggs and melted butter.
Add sour cream and stir well.
Stir in corn and add muffin mix.
Stir until well blended.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: weight watchers enchiladas
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Fill tortillas with mixture. Place in baking dish; cover with shredded cheese and pour chicken bouillon over the top.
(You can reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce for the top.)
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings; 3 proteins; 1 veggie; 2 breads.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice 1/4 inch off stem end of peppers, discarding seeds and membrane.
Cook rice.
Mix rice, spinach, tomato, cheese and pepper.
Spoon into peppers.
Place on 10-inch microwave-safe pie plate.
Microwave on Medium 7 to 9 minutes until peppers begin to soften.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Fry in hot grease.
Eat as is or with syrup.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, slice and boil carrots about 2 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and chill at least 2 hours.
Will keep about 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Fry rice in oil until golden brown.
Add chicken and soy sauce. Add all vegetables and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings
at
each joint and discard tips.
Pat dry. Place on	baking	sheet sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: unfried pies
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Place fruit in the center of each biscuit, fold in half and seal edges with a fork.
Place in a large (greased) baking pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn broiler unit on and brown top of pies.
Remove from oven and brush again with melted butter.

title: cherry glaze(glaze for ham)
directions: Remove ham from oven and stud with cloves.
In small bowl, combine preserves and honey. Spoon over ham surface during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Makes enough glaze for a 4 pound half ham. Double recipe for whole ham.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Mix 3 cups water, bouillon cubes and onions.
Bring to a boil. Add broccoli and simmer 10 minutes.
Add pepper, garlic powder, milk and cheese.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Note:
Have eggs, butter and milk at room temperature.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend in alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Chill 3 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add soup and mushrooms and mix. Remove from heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add sour cream and meat. Add noodles, cooked and drained.
Lightly grease long glass baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and chill the first 4 ingredients until workable, then form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add lemon juice to softened cream cheese.
Add shrimp and green onions, mixing well.
Add enough mayo to give a consistency for dipping.
Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Good for dipping with crackers, chips or raw veggies.

title: frito and bean salad
directions: Shred lettuce and put in a large salad bowl.
Chop tomatoes and add to lettuce.
Drain the chili beans and add to lettuce and tomato.

title: sweet and sour chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use to marinate chicken overnight.

title: easter pineapple stuffing
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.
Cream butter with sugar and beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Remove the crusts from bread and then cube, before adding to mixture (gently).
Pour into greased baking pan. Put foil over the pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes, until the top has browned.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: slush
directions: Boil 2 c. sugar & 7 c. water.
Cool.
Add 4 bags tea to another 2 c. of boiling water.
Leave until water cools.
Remove tea bags. Mix sugar and green Lytm decaf tea water.
Add O.J., lemonade, and brandy.
Freeze overnight.

title: beef taco soup
directions: Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch-wide strips; cut strips in half crosswise.
Place tortilla strips on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until crisp.
Set aside. Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add ground round, onion and garlic; cook until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain beef mixture; pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from pan with a paper towel. Return beef mixture to pan.
Add chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Stir in tomatoes and the next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle soup into individual bowls.
Top evenly with lettuce, tomato, cheese and tortilla strips.
Yields 8 servings.

title: smackeroons
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add vanilla, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets at once.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: french-toasted mozzarella sandwiches
directions: Combine mayonnaise and mustard with onion in a cup.
Spread all bread slices with mixture.
Layer Mozzarella cheese and ham slices on 4 pieces of bread.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs and milk together in a pie plate; dip sandwiches into egg mixture, coating both sides well.
Heat butter or margarine in a skillet; brown sandwiches on both sides until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion. Mix and bring to boil vinegar, sugar, salt and turmeric. Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover tightly. Will keep in refrigerator 1 week.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Fry bacon.
Brown okra and onion in bacon grease.
Add tomatoes and bacon to skillet.
Salt and pepper.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Slice
cake
lengthwise.
Place
side by side.	Put one slice on bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch).
Fill with Cream Filling then fruits.

title: chinese fried walnuts (or pecans)
directions: Bring water to boil; add nuts.
Bring back to boil for 1 minute.
Rinse under hot water in a colander.
Stir in sugar. Heat 1-inch oil in skillet and fry nuts until brown and crispy. Drain on paper towels and salt.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in airtight containers.
I fry in a stock pot and watch the temperature.

title: halloweenies
directions: Boil hot dogs and slice lengthwise.
Lay 4 halves, flat side up next to each other.
Mound with warm mashed potatoes and top with Cheddar cheese.
Broil until melted and bubbly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk, eggs and corn.
Add butter.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shenley's chicken italiano
directions: Cook all ingredients, except chicken, until thick.
Place chicken breasts in covered dish.
Cook 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from heat and uncover.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot over cooked spaghetti.

title: chicken-rice oriental
directions: Saute garlic in oil in skillet until lightly browned.
Add meat, pepper, red pepper or green pepper and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: mommy's oreo cookie ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies; do not remove cream.
Reserve about 3 crushed cookies for top.
Mix rest with butter.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Cover.
Freeze 20 minutes.
Spread softened ice cream. Cover and freeze 20 minutes.
Pour fudge over ice cream.
Cover and freeze for 20 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs.
Freeze overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent roll dough on pizza sheet and bake until lightly browned. Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over crust. Top with chopped vegetables and shredded cheese to your liking.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be stiff, but if too stiff, add more milk.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: In skillet, combine ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat, breaking up meat with a fork until meat is browned and onion and pepper are tender.
Add ketchup, undiluted soup and water.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover top with frozen potato puffs. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes or until potato puffs are golden brown. Serves 4.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: *One tablespoon vinegar in 1/2 cup sweet milk makes buttermilk.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well. Add eggs one at a time. Add milk, flour and salt alternately. Grease large tube pan. Start in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: layered dip
directions: Start with the bean dip.
Spread it on a large platter.
Keep adding layers of the other ingredients.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: grape jelly made from juice
directions: Combine the first three ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat to good, rolling boil.
Add sugar all at once and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: bundt pan gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, measure all ingredients, except confectioners sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended (scrape bowl with spatula often).
Beat 2 minutes on high (scrape bowl occasionally with spatula).

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating approximately 2 minutes between each egg.
Add lemon juice and grated rind.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool. Chill.
Remove side of pan.
Top with fresh fruit or serve plain.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Scald the 2 cups of milk; pour over shortening and sugar in a bowl.
Stir until shortening is melted, then take the 1/2 cup warm water; put yeast into the warm water in the cup.
Stir, then add to mixture in the bowl.
Then add egg (well beaten), then add flour and salt.
Mix well; turn out on counter and knead 5 to 8 times. Put mixture back into bowl; let rise to double its size, then punch down and make into rolls or loaves of bread.
Cover; let rise for 1 to 2 hours, then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place blackberries in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix well and sprinkle over blackberries.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry out on lightly floured surface to 9-inch square.
Place pastry on top of berries.
Trim edges and seal. Make several slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Brush pastry with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips, tossing well.
Pile lightly in well-greased casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry hamburger and onions; then drain most of the fat out.
Put hamburger and onions in pan.
Then mix beans, cheese and barbecue sauce.
Put the Mozzarella cheese all over the top and bake at 350° until cheese is all melted and brown.

title: pollo alla salvia(sage chicken)
directions: Rinse and dry chicken pieces.
Heat oil and butter in a skillet and brown the chicken thoroughly.
Drain most of the fat and add wine to the pan.
Then add Prosciutto and sage.
Season to taste.
Cover and simmer gently until chicken is cooked through, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: outdoor grilled chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Grill.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa and add butter and milk.
Cook over low heat until starts bubbling.
Serve hot over white or yellow cake.

title: matzo meal rolls *
directions: Stir oil into matzo meal.
Mix well.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add to mixture.
Blend. Shape into rolls on greased pan that's been sprinkled with matzo meal.
Bake in preheated 450° to 475° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden.
Yield:
12 large rolls.

title: blueberry cheesecake pie
directions: Stir cream cheese to soften.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into the cream cheese mixture.
Spoon filling into pastry shell.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti. When done, run cold water over to cool.
Add vegetables.
Pour Kraft dressing over mixture. Add salad seasoning. Chill and serve cold.

title: good-morning cookies
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with electric mixer until well combined.
Add flour, applesauce, oats, bran, powdered milk, egg white, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and cloves.
Beat on low speed just until combined.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: "mom's" corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt with fork.
Add both corns.
Put cornstarch in creamed corn can; fill with milk and stir to dissolve.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; cool 5 minutes.
Combine all other ingredients.
Then combine with broccoli and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chips with milk in double boiler over hot water.
Stir until well melted, then add vanilla and walnuts.
Put in well-greased 5 x 7-inch pan.
Chill until firm enough to cut.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese and dry taco mix.
Process until smooth.
Spread on a large tray.
In a separate bowl, mix tomatoes, green pepper, scallions, chili peppers and olives. Spread vegetable mixture on top of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Serve with chips.

title: richard's japanese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon semi-crisp; keep grease.
In a large skillet, combine rice, bacon and egg pieces.
Stir-fry on high heat for 2 minutes.
Add green onions and stems.
Stir-fry for 1 minute. (Use the bacon grease that was left in the skillet for frying.) Serve hot.

title: snowman cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 15 regular-size muffin pan cups and 15 small approximately 1-inch muffin pan cups with cup liners. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spoon batter into muffin cups. Bake 10 to 15 minutes for small cupcakes and 15 to 20 minutes for large cupcakes or until golden and toothpick inserted into centers comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans to racks; cool completely. Remove paper liners.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls together.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake until golden.
Mix next ingredients except veggies.
Spread mixture on crust.
Chop vegetables fine and sprinkle over mixture on crust.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake one hour at 350°.

title: chocolate syrup for ice cream
directions: Boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer for 1 minute.
Store in closed container.

title: o'henry bars(no bake)
directions: In a bowl, mix together the oatmeal, butter or margarine, sugar and syrup.
Spread onto a cookie sheet.
In a saucepan, mix the peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Melt, stirring, until smooth.
Spread on bars.
(Can melt in microwave also.)

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Stir-fry shrimp with scallions and garlic in butter.
Toss and heat thoroughly but quickly (overcooking toughens shrimp).
Add parsley and serve in chafing dish with toothpicks or as a first course.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Blend sugars, egg and butter until creamy.
Add pinto beans and blend well.
Pour into deep 9-inch unbaked shell.
Allow room for filling to cook.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 25 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: old fashioned taffy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small Dutch oven; cook, without stirring, over medium heat, just until mixture reaches soft crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 3 teaspoons for a large cup or 2 teaspoons for a regular cup.

title: hello dollys
directions: Make graham crust in 9 x 10-inch pan. Layer chips, coconut and walnuts.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: hot slaw
directions: Shred cabbage as for cole slaw; set aside.
Cut bacon in pieces; cook to crispness in large frying pan.
When done, remove bacon bits, leaving grease.
To this, add sugar, celery seed, mustard, salt and vinegar.
When this mixture is very hot, add the cabbage, turning it over until well mixed but not cooked.
Add bacon bits.
Serves 4.
(Excellent with hot or cold beef.)

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl with wire whisk. Makes about 7 cups.
Use within 4 to 6 months.

title: divinity candy
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils. Reduce heat; cook without stirring until temperature reaches 248° on candy thermometer or until very small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a firm ball which does not flatten upon removal from water. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Beating constantly on high speed, slowly pour 1/2 hot syrup over egg whites; then cook remaining syrup until temperature reaches 272° on candy thermometer or until small amount of mixture dropped into cold water separates into threads which are hard but not brittle. Beating constantly, pour over first mixture. Beat well after each addition. Continue beating until it loses its gloss. Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper. Good luck. Makes about 40 to 50 pieces.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Lightly beat egg and egg white in a bowl.
Add celery, onion, crumbs, garlic, lemon juice and tuna.
Shape mixture into four patties, using 1/2 cup for each.
Cook patties in oil in large skillet over medium heat 5 minutes until golden brown.
Turn over carefully; cook other side 5 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk, melted margarine, nuts and coconut.
Roll into desired size balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate bits in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Dip balls into mixture and place on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: elizabeth dole apple pie
directions: Put apples, sugar and water in skillet.
Bring to simmer. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup water and stir in apples.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add butter, cinnamon and nutmeg and cool.

title: lunchroom soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and water to desired consistency.
Simmer for 30 to 90 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whip egg yolks, then blend with condensed milk. Add Key lime juice, mixing only until juice is mixed in. Do not overbeat. Pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust. Chill until set (best overnight). Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: eggplant-sausage bake
directions: Cook eggplant, covered, in a small amount of water 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute sausage, celery and onion in a skillet until the sausage is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Drain and set mix aside.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and then meat.
Brown well.
Remove grease.
Add seasoning and chili sauce.
Cook on low, stirring occasionally about 30 minutes.

title: beef stew twists
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add beef cubes and brown on all sides.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, wine vinegar and beef broth. Cover tightly and bake 2 hours.
Cook pasta following box directions.
Remove pan from oven; remove bay leaf.
Blend flour with softened butter.
Stir into beef mixture.
Simmer on stove 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add yogurt and pasta; mix well and serve.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan.
Beat egg yolks and half and half at medium speed of an electric mixer; add to sugar mixture.
Pour hot milk slowly into egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and, if desired, banana extract.
Pour one-third of mixture into baked pastry shell and layer with banana slices.
Repeat layers, ending with filling.
Cover with wax paper; make meringue.
Remove wax paper.
Spread meringue over filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Mix the cocoa, flour and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bananas the night before serving.
Next a.m., dip banana slices in pineapple juice and add to rest of ingredients.
If making for supper, can make in a.m. and let sit in refrigerator all day.

title: party punch
directions: Chill the juices.
Mix and pour over sherbet in punch bowl. Add ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend well the flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and cocoa. Add milk, vanilla and oil; mix until smooth. Add nuts. Spread evenly in a greased 8-inch square cake pan. Mix brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over entire batter. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli for just a few minutes to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Put into casserole.
Cut up cheese over top of broccoli.
Mix crackers and margarine.
Put on top of broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 238° or until small amount forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm, 110°.
Beat until fudge begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Add nuts.

title: elderberry jelly
directions: Remove stems from berries; wash and crush.
Bring to a boil, boiling about 4 minutes.
Strain.
You should have about 3 cups juice.
Using 1 cup of the elderberry juice, grape juice and your choice juice, add lemon juice, sugar and fruit jell pectin.
Bring to a rolling boil for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into canning jar; wipe the tops to make sure they're clean.
Put hot lids and bands on to seal.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Work dough only until well moistened.
Cover and refrigerate to use as needed.
Bake at 400° in oven for about 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, powder, salt and spice.
Add to pumpkin mixture, alternately with water.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into 2 well greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.

title: peanut butter roundups
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugars.	Add eggs, beating well. Add peanut butter; beat well.
Add soda, salt, flour and oats, mixing well.

title: edible play dough (candy)
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in just enough dry milk to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and 1 1/2 cups sugar together (save 1/2 cup sugar).
Make indentation in center.
Add orange juice, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 9 to 10-inch tube pan.
Put in layer of batter, layer apples, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon (in each layer, divided 3 times), ending with apples on top, and sugar on top of apples.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until well done with margarine or butter.
Salt to taste.
Remove chicken from cooker.
Add milk to chicken broth. Let come to a rolling boil.
Add dough about the size of a large biscuit until enough dough is added.
Bring to a rolling boil. Turn down heat; let simmer until done.
Cover with cooker lid.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook squash, green pepper and onion in water and butter just until tender.
Combine with seasonings and soup; stir gently. Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and top is brown.

title: oyster crackers party mix
directions: Mix dressing in small bowl.
Stir all together.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 200°.
Mix every little bit.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook amount spaghetti for your family or who you will be serving. Drain and let cool. Mix all vegetables. In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, milk, vinegar and sugar. Pour over vegetable mixture; mix well. Add spaghetti; toss.

title: joyce's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well, then add sugar and mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Add whole milk to freeze line.
Mix well.

title: banana rama
directions: Fresh peppermint oil or extract is hated by mice.
Drip on cottonball and wipe where mice have been.
They won't come back!

title: blender potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and cut up potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towel. Put all ingredients into blender container; cover.
Press "chop" button for 10 seconds.
Use spatula to push potatoes down, if necessary.
Stop motor when using spatula.

title: noodles
directions: Mix, and roll out thin.
Let dry - then cut.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir mayonnaise with next 5 ingredients until mixed.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce and mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven until hot through and through.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In an oblong pan (sprayed with Pam), spread nuts on the bottom of the pan and place coconut on top of the nuts.
Mix cake mix as per directions; pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar; pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: one bowl chocolate cake(egg free cake)
directions: Mix flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda.
Add oil, vanilla, sugar, vinegar and coffee.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Rectangular pan or lasagna pan can be used.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add tomatoes, chiles and taco seasoning.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Start with flour tortillas and layer with beef then cheese 2 times.
More cheese and chiles may be added to your taste.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes casserole
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese.
Add 4 tablespoons butter, garlic and pepper.
Mix.
Gradually add heavy cream and keep mixing.
Grease pan and top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Beat the powdered sugar, eggs, vanilla and 2 sticks butter for 20 minutes. Spread on crumbs.
Slice bananas lengthwise and place on mixture.
Spread the pineapple on top of the bananas. Spread the Cool Whip on the pineapple. Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Add cherries and chill 8 hours.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add flour and salt.
Knead dough until it is no longer sticky.
Put dough in oiled bowl and let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Grease 2 pizza pans.
Divide dough in half; press in pans, greasing both sides.
Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into buttered 9-inch baking dish.
Cover crumb mixture with diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until thick. Pour this sauce over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve warm plain or with whipped topping.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in water and salt for 15 minutes with cold water. Add milk and boil 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, 3/4 cup sugar and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add to sugar mixture.
Spoon some rice slowly into egg yolk mixture and then slowly add all the rice, mixing well, and let it come to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into a large bowl.
Beat egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on rice and brown in oven at 375°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until light.
Add sugar and blend. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Combine milk and water enough to equal 1 cup.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately to sugar and butter mixture.
Beat in vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour.

title: kraut kuchen
directions: Brown hamburger in large frying pan until half done.
Add cabbage and onion; fry until done on low heat.
Cut off piece of thawed bread, the size of an egg.
Stretch out.
Put spoonful of filling on.
Pinch edges together.
Let rise and bake until done. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vuyna's czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add egg yolks and blend well, about 10 minutes.
Gradually add flour and mix thoroughly. Fold in nuts.
Spoon half the batter into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan; spread evenly.
Top with jam; spread evenly.
Cover with remaining cookie dough.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Delicious! (Baking time may vary according to oven.)

title: olga's cheese cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Knead the ingredients and divide into 2 equal parts.
Let dough set for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts in a flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hr. at 350°.
Good served over brown rice.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring all to boil; remove from heat and let cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Beat sugar and oleo together; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix pie filling and sweetened condensed milk together. Add crushed pineapple. Stir in Cool Whip. Add nuts, if desired. Stir until it's all pink. Store in refrigerator.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Cream together peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Blend in powdered sugar and mix well.
Form into small balls to be dipped in the chocolate.
Now melt the chocolate together with the paraffin in a double boiler.
When completely melted, insert a toothpick into the balls and dip in the chocolate syrup, leaving a small circle uncovered.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store.
Use 1/2 cup of mix with hot water.
Add marshmallows, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes. Combine sour cream and soup. Stir in carrots, onion and zucchini. Combine stuffing and oleo. Spread half of it in the bottom of a 7 x
11-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetables on top.
Place remaining stuffing on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken for 1/2 to 1 hour and debone.
Sprinkle bread crumbs in square pan.
Add cooked broccoli and then spread chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix 1 can of creamed chicken soup and 1/3 cup mayonnaise together.
Smooth over top of chicken.
Spread orange Cheddar cheese (grated) on top.
Then sprinkle bread crumbs and top with some paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, one hour after freezer/refrigerator.

title: bunion burgers
directions: Combine beef, Worcestershire and salt; mix lightly.
Shape into 12 patties.
Top 6 patties with cheese and pickle slices.
Place other 6 patties on top of cheese and pickles and seal edges of top and bottom patties together.
Grill for 5 minutes on each side. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cool melted butter and lemon and anise flavors and orange juice. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Add orange rind and anise seed.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Spray iron with Pam.
Makes 60 Pizzelle.
Serve plain or dust with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Steam broccoli about 5 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy. Thoroughly mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion.
Spoon into baking dish; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut into squares and serve. This is also good cold.

title: lemony asparagus
directions: Snap off and discard woody bases from asparagus. Cook spears in a large skillet for 8 minutes. Drain. Serve on small warmed platter.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Add lemon, salt and thyme. Pour over asparagus.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together (add a little milk to soften).

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Sprinkle miniature marshmallows over warm cake.
Return cake to oven for 2 minutes or until marshmallow are puffed.
In a small bowl combine frosting with chocolate chips and chopped walnuts.
Spread frosting mixture over marshmallow while still warm.
Best when used on a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; beat eggs, oil and buttermilk together and add to dry mix.
Pour a scant cup of batter onto a hot, ungreased waffle iron, baking until golden brown.

title: low-fat snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla, almond extract and Egg Beaters until smooth.
Add flour; blend thoroughly.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: pumpkin oatmeal bran muffins
directions: Beat egg
whites
and 2 teaspoons oil.	Add 1/4 cup oil and pumpkin.
Add
oat bran (soaked in water).	Mix well.
Add sugar and
raisins.
Add	baking powder, soda and spices.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Bake
at
350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 18 muffins. Contains
137 calories, 37 grams fiber, 40 grams fat and 0 milligrams cholesterol.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In casserole dish, combine macaroni, 6 ounces shredded cheese, eggs and milk; stir.
Add remaining cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until melted on top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve and enjoy.

title: pineapple cherry dessert
directions: In baking dish, mix pineapple and pie filling and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour cake mix on top; drizzle oleo on top. Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend the cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
To this mixture, add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and chopped onion and mix well.
Separate the crescent rolls into 8 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into each rectangle and pinch together.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn down to 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes a large cake.
Place a pan of water under the cake while it bakes; will make it more moist.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add melted chocolate squares and blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in three 8-inch greased and floured pans.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: Mix together in a large bowl:
spaghetti sauce, water, kidney beans, corn and chili seasoning mix.
Spread 1 cup of mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange 4 pieces uncooked lasagna over sauce.
Add 1 cup sauce, then 1/2 of Ricotta cheese.
Repeat, ending with remaining sauce.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: baked rabbit
directions: Soak rabbit pieces in 1 1/2 tablespoons of salt water to cover for 2 hours.
Rinse, drain and dry.
Roll in flour and brown in the oil and butter.
Add onion and spices.
Cover tightly and bake in a 325° oven for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Turn rabbit pieces. Add chicken bouillon and water.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs. Beat on high 5 minutes. Add flour, sour cream, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Beat on low until combined. Scrape bowl and beat 1 minute on medium. With spatula, fold in zucchini and chips. Spread batter (will be thick) in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 12 servings (505 calories each).

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook in an unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour over oleo. Pour peaches over mixture in pan.
Mix 4 tablespoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beefaroni
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven; add water, tomatoes, salt and macaroni.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add more water, if needed.
Remove lid and sprinkle with cheese.
Kids love this!

title: seafood stew
directions: Partially thaw crab
meat
and	fish.
Remove skin from fish fillets; cut fillets into 1 inch pieces.
Thoroughly wash clams. Cover clams with salted water using 3 tablespoons salt to 8 cups cold
water.
Let
stand 15 minutes;
rinse.
Repeat twice.

title: easter brunch overnight french toast
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch slices and put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan in single layer.
Beat eggs with other ingredients (except oleo).
Pour this over bread slices and cover pan with foil. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Uncover and dot with small pieces of oleo.
Turn oven on to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together and spread over pineapple.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top of cheese mixture.
Pour melted margarine over the top of the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Take sherbet out of freezer 30 minutes before using.
Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour Sprite over to fill punch bowl.
Mix and serve.
No ice needed.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Shred and mix cabbage, pepper and onion.
Boil for 3 minutes the sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and salad oil.
Add boiled mixture to cabbage mixture while still hot.
Store in covered container in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: chicken souffle
directions: In well greased 10 by 13 pan, cut the crust off bread and put the bread in bottom of pan.
Spread the chicken (seasoned, cooked breasts or thighs) over bread.
Next add the sliced chestnuts, mushrooms and soups.
Next, lay the cheese over top and dot with mayo.
Mix together the eggs, salt, milk, and pimentos.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with buttered bread crumbs sprinkled over the top the last 1/2 hour.
Serves 12 or more and can be frozen.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole ole
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts	in seasoned water until tender. Cool, debone
and cut in bite size pieces.
Line the bottom of a 10
x 13-inch
casserole.
Saute onion and celery in butter and
then add soup, cheese and seasonings.
Simmer sauce until the
cheese melts.
Pour
half	of sauce over chicken.	Layer asparagus over chicken and cover with remaining sauce.
Do not add any
liquid even if it looks dry.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350°
until bubbly.
It
will
serve
12 to 15 people.	It freezes well.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9- inch pan.
Sprinkle over this the cake mix and nuts.
Pour melted butter over this.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done. Cool.
Can use cream cheese filling, Cool Whip or ice cream on top.

title: mrs. truman's ozark pudding
directions: Cream sugar and eggs well.
Add flour and rest of ingredients. Bake in a large Pyrex dish (greased) at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: crab and shrimp au gratin
directions: Cook the shrimp in salted water 3 minutes. Drain.
Saute mushrooms, garlic and onion in butter for 5 minutes. Stir in flour, pepper and dill, then stir in milk.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add half of the cheese. Stir until melted.
Add white wine.
Mix lightly the crab and artichokes with the other mixture and the rest of the cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside for topping.
Cream together oil, egg and sugar.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate almond peach drink
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 65 calories.

title: beef-barley stew
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery in a nonstick Dutch oven, stirring frequently, until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, breaking up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until barley is tender and stew is desired consistency.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bundt vegetable bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry and crumble bacon; drain off fat for something else.
Melt oleo and saute celery, onion and pepper in oleo.
Cut biscuits in 6 pieces each.
Mix everything in a large bowl.
Put in Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Will look lumpy.
Bake at 340° for 30 minutes or less until browned.
Good with lite butter or sour cream:
(1/3 cup milk, 3 tablespoons of lemon juice, 1 cup low-fat cottage cheese).
Mix together in blender.
Can be frozen.

title: original italian lasagna
directions: Brown beef in frying pan.
In saucepan empty cans of paste. To each large can of paste add 1 can of water and to each small can add 2 cans of water.
Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In a blender: basil leaves, nuts and garlic.
Blend until fine.
Then: add oil in a thin stream while blending.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Serve over hot pasta, which was boiled "al dente."

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl; make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips, 2 inches long.
In large skillet, brown meat; turn frequently.
Stir in mix and 2 cups of water. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: oven baked chicken(serves 4)
directions: Marinate chicken in buttermilk overnight.
In a large bowl, combine flour, Parmesan cheese, herbs, spices, salt and pepper. Roll each chicken piece in spicy flour mixture and place on a rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Combine beef with corn, soup, pimento and 2 cups cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rice and cornbread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in banana, egg whites and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and place in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients except for jalapenos.
Do not cover. Microwave on High for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Add jalapenos and microwave another 3 minutes, or until it just begins to boil, stirring once.
Drain off excess liquid and refrigerate to chill. Serve cold with tortilla chips or poultry.

title: zucchini freezer jam
directions: Place zucchini in a pan with a very small amount of water. Cook 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sugar, pineapples and juice and lemon juice.
Place back on heat and bring to a boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in apricot Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in freezer containers and seal.
Let set one day and store in freezer.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Roll vanilla wafers fine.
Add melted butter.
Mix well. Soften cream cheese and whip.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Whip Dream Whip with cold milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Top with rest of vanilla wafer mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: "hamlins" hot sauce
directions: Grind onions and hot peppers.
Squash up tomatoes.
Mix all together.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 hours.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Pat softened cookie dough into a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream cheese with powdered sugar; spread over cooked dough.
Add sliced fruit by rows:
grapes, oranges, bananas, strawberries, peaches and kiwi. Warm lemon juice, water and preserves.
Spread over fruit. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: baked ham with pineapple
directions: Remove and discard casing from ham. Score top of ham in a diamond design and stud with cloves.
Place ham in a shallow baking dish and arrange pineapple slices over top.
Pour ginger ale over ham and evenly sprinkle each pineapple slice with cinnamon. Bake ham at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated. Cut into 12 slices and serve.
Exchanges:
2 meats.

title: caramel custard
directions: Gently stir 1/3 cup sugar over a low heat in a heavy skillet until sugar melts and is a golden syrup.
Immediately pour syrup into bottom of six custard cups.
Beat eggs until bubbly.
Slowly add remaining sugar into beaten eggs and mix well.
Stir in salt. Slowly heat milk until a film forms across the top (this is called scalding).
Do not boil!
Gradually pour milk into egg and sugar mixture.
Be sure to stir constantly while pouring in the milk so the eggs do not cook.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Set oven at 325°. Carefully pour custard mixture into cups.
Place in baking dish. Add boiling water to depth of 1/2 the cup.
Bake for 40 minutes or until silver knife inserted in edge comes out clean.

title: chuck wagon
directions: Mix together in frying pan.
After it's all fried up put in a big dish, cover with shredded pizza cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn dogs
directions: Melt fat or oil for frying.
Combine corn meal, flour and seasoning.
Blend egg, 1/4 cup milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix lightly.
Add more milk if needed to make thick batter.
Dip wieners in batter and fry in deep hot fat about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Insert sticks in one end of wiener if desired.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt shortening on low heat; add milk, salt and 1/3 cup sugar. When cooked, add 3 cups flour.
Reserve 2 more for later.

title: macy's stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Do not wrap in foil. When done, cut in half lengthwise and scoop out inside.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk.
Beat in cool whip.
Beat in softened cream cheese.
Roll out frozen oreos into consistency of dirt (processor okay to use).
Alternate dirt and pudding.
Start and end with dirt layer.
Put gummie worms, etc. through the layers as you are
layering pudding and dirt.
Refrigerate for 3 hours. Stick in flower and serve with a trowel.

title: neiman-marcus butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter.
Mix well and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread batter evenly. Mix the remaining 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over the first layer and smooth evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
It usually does not look done.

title: oreo dirt
directions: Put 1/2 crumbs in bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk and pudding.
Let thicken.
Mix together pudding and cheese mixture and Cool Whip.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Let chill several hours.

title: yogurt smoothie
directions: Serves 7 to 8 cups.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease sides and bottom of Bundt pan.
Break rolls in three and drop in pan.

title: dilled beans and squash
directions: Trim ends off green beans.
Cut squash in thin slices, 3-inches long.
Cook beans in water, covered, for 3 minutes.
Add squash.
Cook 2 minutes longer or until beans are tender.
Drain well.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except cucumbers.
Let cool, then pour over cucumbers that have been placed into a gallon jar. Put in refrigerator; let set about 2 weeks before eating.

title: chewy coconut bars(you can't eat just one!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In large bowl, cream the shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract. Slowly blend in flour, baking powder and salt. Mix until well blended. Fold in chocolate chips, walnuts and coconut. Spread the mixture evenly in pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool before cutting into bars. Makes 18 bars.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Cook giblet and neck with stalk of celery for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 4 cups of water.
Remove from heat and pick meat from neck and chop giblets.
Reserve broth.
Combine drippings and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add giblet stock and eggs while cooking over low to medium heat.
Cook until desired thickness.
Stir in meat pieces.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Add orange juice to bring to desired consistency.
Refrigerate.

title: lori's caramel apple snack
directions: Soften cream cheese; place in the center of a 9 or 10-inch plate, or in a small bowl if you prefer.
After carefully washing the apples, cut into bite size wedges (8 to 10 wedges per apple). Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh to prevent darkening.
Pour a generous amount of caramel topping over cream cheese and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Arrange apples around the cream cheese.
Dip the apples into the cream cheese, being sure to include the topping. The taste is a delicious surprise!

title: baked beans
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Put into baking dish and add the rest of ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 16-inch ungreased pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in a 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 300 until done, about 50 to 55 minutes; test with toothpick.

title: quick skillet supper with gravy
directions: Brown meat in electric skillet or large frying pan in oil or drippings.
Add soup and water.
Cover and simmer until meat is fork-tender (about 1 hour).
Continue to add water as needed to make gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook cornbread and rice as usual; set aside.
Clean peppers and halve, then put in pan of water and boil for 10 minutes.
When peppers have boiled, drain on paper towel.
Brown ground beef, onion and some bell pepper bits until beef is done.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients together and fill peppers.
Place strips of bacon on peppers and bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Can also use chicken broth to get desired consistency.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat; add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cook until tomatoes are mixed in well.
Cook potatoes by package directions.
Place meat mixture in casserole.
Top with potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: can't count calories cheeseburgers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
You can shape these into patties to fry on the stove, bake in the oven or sizzle on the grill.
This recipe also can be used as a meat loaf or as meat balls for spaghetti sauce.
You may put on your favorite slice of cheese, if you desire cheeseburgers, or serve plain. Fry, bake or grill to the doneness that you desire, then serve plain or with your favorite entree.
Sit back, smile and enjoy, but please, you can't count the calories with this recipe for my cheeseburgers!

title: candy-covered nuts
directions: Mix together and boil to soft ball stage.
Stir in nuts.
Coat the nuts; spread on wax paper to cool.

title: greens, peas and cheese salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place half the greens, onion, peas and cheese.
Sprinkle with half the sugar.
Dot with 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Add bacon and toss just before serving.

title: homecoming banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix vanilla pudding according to directions and add 3/4 of the cool whip.
Blend until smooth.
In another large bowl, place wafers, sliced bananas and cover with pudding and continue to layer the wafers, bananas, and pudding until all is used and top with 1/4 of the cool whip.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water, drain and mash.
Saute onion, garlic and pepper in bacon grease.
Add eggplant and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs, egg, milk, butter, salt and pepper (to taste).
Pour into casserole dish, sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine rye flour, yeast and 3 1/2 cups white flour in large bowl.
Stir to mix.
Combine salt, margarine, molasses, milk and water in saucepan and heat to very warm (approximately 130°).
Add heated liquid to the flour-yeast mixture.
Stir to moisten.
Use as much of the cup of white flour to knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Knead and divide into 2 balls.
Shape into long loaves.
Place on a greased baking sheet and cover with dry towel.
Let rise until doubled.
Brush with egg white diluted with 1 tablespoon water.
With a sharp knife lightly cut diagonally across top of each loaf 3 times.
Sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: red beans and rice("cajun")
directions: Cook overnight in crock-pot.
Cook 2 cups rice.
Serve sausage mixture over rice.
Very good on cold day.

title: evelyn's cheese cake
directions: Combine the first 4 dry ingredients.
Add eggs and melted butter.
Mix all the above ingredients.
Pat it into and up the sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pipe down pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops over the potatoes.
Combine the soups and pour over the pork chops and potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.
(Taken from Aunt Bee's Mayberry Cookbook)

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Good with fresh fruits.

title: bohemian kolachy
directions: Crumble yeast in water with sugar; let stand until dissolved. Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine as for pie crust; add egg yolks, sour cream and yeast.
Knead to soft dough; refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on lightly floured board to about 1/2-inch. Cut small circles with doughnut cutter; put on cookie sheet, rounds touching.
Let rise until double.
Make imprint in center of each and fill with pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken mexican casserole
directions: Put everything in a pan, except Doritos; let mixture get hot. Mix well.
Pour crushed Doritos in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in mixture.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven at 350° and bake until cheese is melted.

title: honey-orange syrup
directions: Heat honey, orange juice and margarine until margarine melts and syrup is warm.
Store in honey-type squeeze bottle (for easy heating and pouring).
Serve warm over pancakes or waffles.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fried apples - bryant style
directions: Core apples (do not peel) and cut into sixths.
In skillet, melt margarine.
Add apples, sugar, vinegar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cinnamon candies.
(Candies are for red color as well as flavor.)
Cook slowly (mostly uncovered) for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The apples will have cooked out part of their juices. Stir carefully and occasionally.

title: san's five bean chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until opaque.
Add meats and brown thoroughly.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, beer and beans to meat and bring to a simmer.
Simmer uncovered for 5 to 7 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Taste after 30 minutes, adjusting seasonings to taste.
Simmer for 15 to 20 more minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Garnish with grated Monterey Jack cheese, chopped onions or jalapenos.
Goes great with corn bread!
Enjoy!

title: easiest mexican dip
directions: In a deep skillet, brown ground beef on medium high.
Just before it is done, drain and put back in skillet.
Add cheese. Cover and turn down temperature to a low simmer.
(Be careful not to burn the cheese!)
When cheese is completely melted, add entire jar of salsa, stir well and serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandmother's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and flour the fruit and nuts in additional flour.

The ingredients may be combined in order given, eggs being added alternately with flour, each egg being beaten in well, or eggs may be separated, the yolks alternately with flour and whites stiffly beaten and folded in before fruit and nuts are added.
Place dough in loaf pans lined with layer of heavy waxed paper or with 4 layers thin waxed paper. Bake at 350°.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions, using sheet cake pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lg. bowl; tossing to coat. Cover and refrigerate
8 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake cools, divide cake into four parts.
After dividing, cut cake into 1-inch pieces.
Prepare jello as directed, substituting frozen strawberries for cold water.
Set aside.
Prepare instant pudding as directed.
Layer in a large punch bowl or trifle bowl as follows: jello-strawberry mixture, cake, pudding.
Repeat layers until done.
Spread top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle top with slivered almonds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with herb dressing until well coated.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Line greased casserole dish with 1/2 of the dressing.
Pour mixed ingredients over this; sprinkle remaining dressing on top.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Casserole serves 16.

title: six-herb dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with raw vegetables.
May also be used as salad dressing.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Boil
chicken breasts.	When
done,
remove
broth
and save. To make the gravy:	Melt the Crisco and add the paprika and flour, stirring until
well
blended.
This will be thick. Add to this the chicken
broth.
This makes a nice gravy.
Set aside to cool. Add the
sour
cream to the cooled gravy.
Put the chicken breasts in	the
gravy
and heat through and serve with spaetzle or noodles.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add molasses, then all dry ingredients along with hot water.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Put meat strips in bowl; add 1 tablespoon soy sauce, next 3 ingredients and 2 tablespoons oil.
Set aside.
Mix remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce with sesame oil; set aside.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in uncovered wok at 400°.
Add garlic; stir-fry 10 seconds.
Add beef; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add onion and sesame oil mixture; stir-fry until heated through, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately, over hot cooked rice.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to gelatin; mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into gelatin mixture carefully.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together cooked and well-drained spinach with all other ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll into walnut-size balls and lay single on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Makes about 50 balls.

title: picadillo
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Saute over medium-high heat with crushed garlic until onion and pepper are tender.
Add hamburger and brown on high heat until meat is cooked through.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and salt and garlic to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes until mixture is very thick and water is cooked out.
Coarsely chop olives; add to meat and cook for about 5 minutes.
Serve over yellow rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry 'n cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Fold in pineapple and bananas.
Pour in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix together peanut butter, 1 1/2 sticks butter or margarine and powdered sugar and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and pepper.
Cook until lightly browned.
Remove chicken.
Add onion, garlic and 1/4 cup chicken broth to skillet; cook until softened.
Add tomato, basil and thyme; cook for 3 minutes.
Add wine and remaining 1/4 cup chicken broth; increase heat to high and bring to boil.
Return chicken; add olives and reduce to medium heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through.
Add cornstarch mixture, stirring until slightly thickened.
Serve garnished with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine sour cream and taco mix and spread onto bottom of square pan.
Top with layer of fresh onions, tomatoes, shredded lettuce, and heaps of Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: island chicken salad pitas
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use enough mayonnaise to make salad the consistency you like.
Curry powder and chutney can be varied according to taste.
Preferably, use a mango-based chutney, such as Major Gray's.
To serve, scoop salad into pita pockets.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic; cook until light brown.
Add shrimp, crab and mushrooms.
Saute until mushrooms are slightly limp.
Add lemon juice and cream.
Bring to high temperature, but don't boil. Add yolks and whip to make sauce.
Add fettucini, cheese and parsley; stir well.
Serve garlic bread with this.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sloppy joe sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling and then simmer 45 minutes.
Spoon into hamburg buns. Best when made a day ahead.
Makes 10 to 12 sandwiches.

title: mist brisket
directions: Heat Irish Mist in small pan; add prunes, and set aside to seep.
Brown brisket, onions and celery in small amount of shortening or oil.
Transfer to roasting pan and sprinkle with seasoned salt, pepper, ginger and Worcestershire sauce as desired. Combine water, lemon juice and brown sugar; add to pan.
Cover tightly and roast 325° for 1 hour.
Add prunes with the Irish Mist and carrots.
Cover and roast for 2 hours or until meat is fork tender.
To serve, slice brisket across grain.
Serve with boiled new potatoes and cabbage edges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in large bowl.
Add shortening and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Turn mixer on low until all is moistened.
Beat for full 10 minutes on medium speed.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add the beaten egg.
Measure and sift the dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with hot water.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid a little at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Bake in a 350° oven in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soup and milk.
Remove chicken from bones. Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soup and milk over the chicken.
Mix the dressing with the chicken broth as if you were going to bake it. Spoon dressing over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Put the first four dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, mix together margarine, cocoa and water; bring to boil. Then pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat well.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break or cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Combine broccoli, onion, crumbled bacon and raisins.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing.
Mix dressing in with other ingredients.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: old fashioned spoon bread
directions: Scald milk and slowly add corn meal, sugar and salt.
Cook until it "puffs", stirring constantly.
Set off the stove and add butter.
Allow to cool for 3 minutes.
Stir in well beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the 7-Up.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.

title: fruit juice fizz
directions: Cut the orange into slices.
Put 1 C. of each juice into pitcher. For every 3 C. of juice, add 1 C. of Sprite.
Add sliced oranges. Chill and serve.

title: extra gooey fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to
Melt chocolate and butter together in microwave or
double
boiler.
Remove
from
heat
and stir together until smooth
and blended.
Let cool to room temperature. Lightly grease 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples to cover about 2-inches in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle over the apples the sugar, flour and cinnamon. Mix and sprinkle on top the oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, margarine, soda and baking powder. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Mix broth and mustard in deep pan.
Stir in seeds and bring to boil.
Add potatoes and onion.
Reduce to medium heat; cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add kielbasa and cabbage.
Cover and cook 15 more minutes.
Stir in apple; cover and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: hank snow's favorite strawberry pie
directions: Simmer water, sugar and cornstarch until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O mixture and stir until dissolved.
Layer strawberry slices in bottom of crust.
Pour pie filling over strawberries and refrigerate.
Serve chilled with whipped cream topping.

title: garbage cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together in order except the last ingredient. Mix well and then stir in last ingredient. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for about 8 minutes.

title: mamma kelly's 4-way cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and dry ingredients. Add vanilla.
Chill.
Divide dough into four parts.
To each portion of dough, add one of these ingredients:
nuts, coconut, chocolate chips or cocoa and lemon zest.
Make rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and tinfoil.
Chill or freeze until ready to bake.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 10 dozen.

title: egg yolk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well.
Add baking powder, salt and flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
My oven takes only 1 1/4 hours.
Freeze if desired.

title: quick and easy donuts
directions: Will also need bottle cap (aspirin bottle cap will do) and paper bag.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add sugar to apples, stir to combine, let stand 10 minutes. Sift flour with salt and spices and soda.
Blend oil and egg into apple mixture.
Add flour mix, stirring until just blended, fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into waxed paper lined (greased the paper) 9-inch square or round pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar or serve warm with vanilla ice cream or double the recipe, making 2 cakes and ice with cream cheese icing.

title: homemade chop suey
directions: Cook pork in skillet until browned with garlic and some onion.
Add broccoli or spinach, fresh tomatoes and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until broccoli or spinach is done.
Can add bean sprouts and water chestnuts, if desired.
Serve over rice; add soy sauce on plates and eat.
Takes about an hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
and
drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion;
then
mix
with
broccoli.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Mix melted margarine with stuffing and
put on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix together first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with nut mixture.
Pour half of the batter on top of the nuts.
Sprinkle with nuts on top of cake mixture.
Pour in remaining batter.
Sprinkle rest of nuts on mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Turn out immediately.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes over medium heat in enough water to cover until just tender.
Drain in colander.
Rinse with cold water.
Use electric mixer to mash potatoes.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper to taste and mix until smooth.

title: bev's georgetown eggnog
directions: Mix together in an unlined pumpkin shell and add 1 jar spiced red apple rings (juice and all).
Tie a piece of dry ice in a small net bag.
Cut up on old onion bag or the like and drop it in the punch just before serving. (It will chill the punch and give off a beautiful and harmless, spooky mist at the same time.)
Dry ice can be bought at Joe's Ice on Plymouth Road in Detroit or at most ice cream stores.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind squash, onions and green peppers; mix together.
Add the salt.
Cover with cold water and let stand 1 hour.
Put vinegar, sugar and spices together and boil 3 minutes.
Add drained squash. Don't wash off the salt.
Simmer together for 5 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: angela's cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually add sugar.
Mix in vanilla and sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip; put in crust.
Chill 4 hours.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk and peanut butter chips.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pour over crust.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 65 minutes or until set.
Cool in oven with door slightly ajar for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: delicious banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip and wafers.
This makes a large dish.
May be halved for a small family.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add one or two pieces of chicken at a time in the bag and shake to coat thoroughly.
In large frypan, place oil and heat to high temperature (425°).
Add chicken, skin side down, and cook for 10 minutes, turning often or until brown on all sides.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook about 20 minutes longer or until fork inserts into chicken with ease.
Serves 4.

title: angel pie
directions: Add baking powder and nuts to crumbs and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and flavoring to egg whites.
