Fold in dry ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured pie pan; bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: easy crab spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on dinner plate and pour bottle of cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Crumble crab meat on top of the cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; gradually add powdered sugar. Cream well. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Sift flour with soda and cream of tartar. Stir in pecans. Drop small spoonfuls (or shape into small balls) on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until creamy tan. If you like, roll in powdered sugar while hot. Makes 6 1/2 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Blend at low speed until completely moistened (about 1 minute).
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bubble coffee cake
directions: Layer first four ingredients in bottom of Bundt pan.
Melt oleo.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Dip Rhodes dinner rolls into oleo and then in sugar mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan. Cover and let rise for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool 15 to 20 minutes and remove from pan.

title: katie gooch wilmot's red devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and beat.
Add boiling water to cocoa, then add to sugar and butter mixture.
Then vanilla and flour.
Put soda in sour milk or clabber and stir well.
Add last to first mixture.
Grease and flour two round cake pans.
Use a bit of flour and cocoa so as not to leave a white crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean from center.
Ice with a chocolate icing.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, applesauce, eggs, cocoa and coffee.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and then vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli green rice
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix with water, soup and broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour cheese over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: "killer" brownies
directions: Melt butter and 1/3 cup milk together.
Mix this with cake mix. Put 1/2 mixture in a 7 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt caramels and rest of milk together.
Spread chocolate chips on baked cake mixture.
Cover with caramel mixture. Spread rest of cake mixture on top of all this and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Bake one day ahead.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup. Boil until syrup will form thread. Pour syrup into 3 egg whites, beaten stiff. Pour slowly and continue beating until all syrup is added. Continue beating until mixture begins to get stiff. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and chopped pecans. Drop by teaspoon on foil or wax paper.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce to 325°.
In saucepan over low heat melt chips with butter.

title: lemon 7-up jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add crushed pineapple, 7-Up, marshmallows and bananas.
Chill until firm.
In a small saucepan, mix sugar and flour.
Add reserved pineapple juice and egg; cook until boiling, stirring.
Take off heat and add butter and prepared Dream Whip.
Spread on jello.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken, water, celery, onion and seasoning in Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove chicken and strain liquid.
Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut meat in small pieces.
Return stock to Dutch oven.
Add noodles.
Cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken, meat and parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soup, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Add chopped chicken.
Break up spaghetti over this and pour broth over all.
Boil, cut to low and cook 10 minutes.
Put in casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: martha's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and peanut butter until it comes to a boil. Don't cook	very
long.
Add vanilla and cereal.
Place on cookie sheet
by
spoonfuls
and
cool
if
you
can before someone eats it!

title: carrot-raisin slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine the carrots, raisins and red pepper. Toss. Add the parsley and cumin; toss again. Add the vinegar, honey, salt and pepper. Toss one more time.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cereal brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Spoon on cookie sheet.
Top with pecans and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: short cut chili sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onion, green pepper and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain in colander; do not press vegetables. Place vegetable mixture in kettle.
Add sugar, brown sugar, pepper, mixed spices (in a cloth) and vinegar.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald the 3 cups of milk; stir in cornmeal and molasses.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add everything but cold milk.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Add cold milk; do not stir. Continue baking at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Put everything in a food processor and blend.
Bake in pie pan at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh blueberry-peach pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and lemon rind.
Whisk in 1 cup water until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until mixture is boiling and thickened.
Gently fold in peaches and blueberries.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: garden, beef and rice dish
directions: In a saucepan, brown ground beef.
Cook onion and garlic (use shortening, if needed).
Stir to separate meat; pour off fat.
Add vegetable soup, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and rice.
Bring to a boil; stir and cover.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir often.
After cooking, to keep warm, place in warm oven until served.
Makes 3 cups.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Use 1/2 can mushroom soup in bottom of dish.
Layer asparagus, peas, 1/2 of eggs and crushed crackers; alternate the same for the second layer.
Mix the other half of soup with asparagus juice and pour over the top.
Take a knife and pull mixture away from sides of casserole dish so liquid can be absorbed.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basghetti
directions: Make the whole hamburger; cut it up.
Make noodles.
Put grease in pot and put noodles in there.
Turn stove on for half an hour and cook noodles.
When it's done past the half an hour you can take the noodles out.
Cook hamburger for 2 hours.
When it's done you put the hamburger into the noodles and then put some hot sauce onto it-whatever kind you want and that's all.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add water; sprinkle sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange nuts and coconut on sugar mixture.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes for topping to begin to set.
Turn upside down onto large plate or cookie sheet.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: angel pillows
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Set aside.
Cream 1/2 cup Crisco, cream cheese and milk in medium bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in brown sugar. Beat in 1/2 cup preserves.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Drop 2 level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough into a mound to form each cookie.
Place 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake for 14 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack. Cool completely before frosting.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Pare and remove seeds from cucumbers.
Cut into large chunks; salt.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Mix remainder of ingredients in saucepan.
Add the cucumbers.
Simmer until the cucumbers are easily pierced with a fork.
Pack them in jars and cover with syrup.

title: b l t pizza
directions: Spread Ranch dressing over baked pizza dough.
Layer remaining ingredients (lettuce, tomatoes, bacon and cheese).
Chill up to 2 hours.
After that, it becomes soggy.
(Can add carrots, mushrooms, broccoli and peppers before bacon and cheese.)

title: chocolate mint wafers
directions: Cream butter.
Add soda, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add egg, beaten well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Place dough in refrigerator to chill; roll thin on floured canvas and cut with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen double cookies.
Put cookies together with mint frosting.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread cake
directions: About 3 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-cup fluted baking mold or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients, except confectioners sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, scraping occasionally. Pour batter into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack completely. Sift confectioners sugar on top before serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let stand to enhance flavor, preferably overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan, line bottom with wax paper, grease paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt.
In a large bowl cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time until fluffy again.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Fold in pecans and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a preheated oven to 325° for one hour and 20 minutes or until golden and a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Loosen around edges with a knife.
Turn out onto rack.
Peel off waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese and beef upside-down cornbread
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add beef and onion; cook until beef is lightly browned.
Stir in flour.
Add tomato paste, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and olives.
Spread evenly over bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread over beef mixture.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen around edges and invert onto a serving platter.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix with 1 cup sour cream and garnish with nuts.

title: big red ice cream
directions: Blend a little Big Red with both cans of Eagle Brand milk using a mixer.
Pour mixture in freezer containers, then pour remaining Big Red.
It's ready to freeze.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and sugar. In pan, combine butter, cocoa and Coke.
Heat to boiling and cool. Pour over flour and sugar.
Stir. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Add marshmallows.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and frost while cake is still hot.

title: pennsylvania dutch pot pie
directions: Brown turkey or chicken in butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Mix milk with gravy mix; pour over turkey or chicken.
Add frozen vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 4 ounces egg noodles, cooked.

title: panzanella(italian tomato and bread salad)
directions: Put bread slices into a large bowl.
Add cold water to cover; let soak 10 minutes.
In another bowl, whisk oil, vinegar, salt, garlic and pepper until blended.
Drain bread and press out excess water.
Tear into small pieces and add olive oil and wine vinegar to mixture.
Add tomatoes and onion; toss to mix.
Let stand at least 30 minutes or up to 4 hours.
Stir in basil before serving. Garnish with basil leaves.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Amounts can be adjusted to your desire.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Drain.
Pour sauce in a large casserole dish.
Place a mixture of cheese, meat and onion inside each tortilla.
Roll up and place on sauce.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over dish.
Heat at 350° until warm and cheese melts, about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook
spaghetti;
drain.
Stir
margarine into hot spaghetti. Stir
in
Parmesan
and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust"
in a buttered pie plate.
In a skillet, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain excess fat and add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar and garlic salt.
Heat and cook until
bubbly. Spread
cottage cheese over the crust.
Spread meat
sauce
over the
cottage
cheese.
Top with Mozzarella. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together the chicken, broth, soup and vegetables.
Spread in oblong baking dish.

title: minestrone soup-nancy luthy
directions: Prepare pasta.
Chop onion and carrots.
Slice cabbage coarsely (about 8 cups).
Over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion and carrots until tender.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, instant broth and 6 cups water.
Heat to boiling and reduce to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until cabbage is very tender.
Add cooked pasta, red and white kidney beans with their liquid, frozen spinach and seasonings.
Over high heat, cook until spinach is completely thawed and mixture is hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine cooked hamburger, onion, canned items and taco seasoning.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: fritz's easy cheese sausage squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage with onion.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
In large bowl, add pancake mix, eggs, drained sausage mixture, Ricotta, Mozzarella, basil and parsley.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle lightly with grated cheese.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, using a wire whisk.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt, then add reserved mixture.
Batter will be lumpy.
Add blueberries.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together; pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Recipe can be doubled, but should be baked in 2 pans. Serves 6.

title: mauna's favorite fruit salad
directions: Combine the apple, raisins, celery, and walnuts.
Mix well. In small bowl, combine the Cool Whip with the mayonnaise.
Mix well and stir into fruit salad.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: raspberry bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix flour and cinnamon, soda and salt. Make well in the center.
In separate bowl, mash thawed, drained raspberries with sugar.
Add eggs and oil.
Pour in flour mixture well.
Mix well. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake one hour.
Serve with cream cheese or fruit butter.

title: banana bread
directions: Lightly grease bottom only of a loaf pan.
Blend all ingredients on medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: long island ice teas(alcohlic beverages)
directions: For one drink, combine all preceding ingredients and shake.

title: texas jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in jam and preserves.
Stir together dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to jam mixture. Turn into well-greased and floured pans (three 9-inch pans).
Bake for 40 minutes, or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with Maple Frosting.
Garnish with nuts, if desired.

title: christmas jello mold
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add gelatin, lemon juice, strawberries and red food coloring.
Place 1/3 of mixture into mold.
Tupperware works well.
Set until firm.
Add green food coloring to sour cream, place on top of set mold.
Spoon the rest of jello over mold.
Set until firm.
Great to bring to a Christmas party!

title: cajun coq au vin
directions: Brown chicken
in
butter.
Add
onions, shallots, carrots, garlic, fresh and dry parsley, minced onions and brandy. Stir for 10
minutes.
Add
peppers,
thyme,
bay leaf, flour, bacon, salt and
pepper.
After
10 minutes, add wine and cook for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Add mushrooms after 1 hour.
Add water as needed; season to taste.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix together soft bread crumbs, ground meat, milk, salt and pepper and shape into meat balls.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, sugar, water, catsup and onions.
Pour over meat balls.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Cook with top on so there is more juice.
Can be made a day ahead.
When ready to use, take off grease before reheating.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk; add beef, green pepper, onion and sour cream.
Place in pie plate.
Saute pecans in butter and sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Bake pie shell 5 minutes in 350° oven.
Combine sugar, flour, oleo, salt and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth; add lemon juice and milk and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold into first mixture.
Pour into cooled pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until filling is firm.
This bakes like a cake but the inside is like a pie.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff, then add sugar and vanilla.
Slowly fold in crushed crackers.
Pour batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool, then spread on blueberry pie, topped with Dream Whip and nuts.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick butter and 1 egg.
Pat into pan, 9 x 13. Mix together powdered sugar, 1 stick butter, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over top of other mixture.
Bake 55 minutes at 300°. Top with pecans.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, salt, milk and yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Then add the mixture to the beaten egg whites and add remaining ingredients.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 9 items together and put in casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese and potato chips.
Heat in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breast to 1/2 thickness and lay on cookie sheet.
Combine mustard and dill in small bowl. Mix well spread mustard mixture evenly over the inside of chicken breast.
Top each breast with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Then tuck and roll them up.
Place beaten eggs in a flat dish and bread crumbs in another.
Dip rolls into the beaten eggs, then the bread crumbs.
Heat margarine in skillet and saute until golden brown. Place breast into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that's been coated with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake for 25 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Combine the first three ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hommos bi tahini
directions: Add finely minced garlic and salt to tahini.
Mix in lime juice until completely absorbed.
Add water and mix.
Set aside. Blend garbanzo beans in a blender or food processor until they are smooth.
Add garbanzos to tahini mixture, then the cayenne.
Add some of the reserved bean juice if consistency is too thick.
Add more salt or cayenne if necessary and put in a wide shallow bowl. Spread with olive oil and sprinkle with chopped cilantro.
Serve with warm pita bread.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice with water on medium heat until all water is gone. Turn to low.
Stir the rice.
Cover for 15 to 20 minutes; set aside.
Beat eggs, one at a time; fry in large skillet with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cut into strips and set aside.
Chop onion; fry in small amount of oil until it is clear.
To this, add the chopped meat of choice and cook until the meat is done.
Set aside.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Slice oranges into quarters.
Core and quarter apples.
Grind cranberries, oranges and apples in grinder with coarse blade or in food processor.
Add sugar. Adjust to taste.
Best if made 2 weeks in advance.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep 8 to 10 months in airtight container.

title: ranger pie
directions: Mix by hand eggs, sugar, flour, margarine, pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set and brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Do not peel.
Slice onions. Dissolve salt in water and pour over sliced vegetables.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices and bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat to boiling point, do not boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, water and sugar together in saucepan. Cook until thick; add jello.
Stir well and let cool.
Pour over peaches in baked pie shell.

title: sticky pull-apart rolls
directions: Thaw bread overnight in refrigerator.
Mix all other ingredients in pan.
Heat on low until butter is melted and everything is well mixed.
Do not heat to a boil.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tear loaf of bread dough into small pieces and put in cake pan.
Pour pudding mixture over the bread pieces.
Tear second loaf and put on top of poured mixture.
Cover and let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn over onto cookie sheet.
Let it sit 5 minutes before removing the pan.

title: chow chow
directions: Cut cauliflower in flowerets and parboil in salted water. Cool.
Cut pickles in pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for approximately 1 day in icebox.
Mix and stir 2 or 3 times during the day.
Put into jars.

title: cold mac salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together thoroughly, then mix with macaroni and refrigerate.

title: peach pie
directions: Bring sugar,
starch,
syrup
and water to a boil.
Add and dissolve
gelatin.	Cool mixture until it begins to thicken.

title: diet jam
directions: Combine fruit, gelatin, apple juice and sweetener.
Cook 20 minutes or until fruit is done. Add sure-jell.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
Try these combinations:
peaches and raspberry gelatin, apple and orange gelatin, or figs and strawberry gelatin.

title: stuffed meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients, except catsup, mushrooms and cheese; mix just
until
combined (do not overmix).
Spread on wax paper to
form
a
x
12-inch
rectangle about 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle
cheese and mushrooms over meat.
Then, using wax paper to start, roll meat, jelly roll fashion.
Place seam down on roasting
rack.
Spread
catsup
on top.
Cook, uncovered, about 16	minutes
on High.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: dessert cheese centerpiece
directions: Beat together cottage cheese, cream cheese and Blue cheese until they are smooth and creamy.
Gradually beat in whipping cream, beating until thickened.
Stand colander in a bowl and line with several thicknesses of cheesecloth.
Pour in cheese mixture. Tie cheesecloth at top.
Let drain overnight in refrigerator. Untie cloth and turn ball out onto a plate.
Remove cloth. Decorate top of cheese with lemon or mint leaves.
Surround cheese with assorted crackers, apples and pears.
Brush fruit lightly with lemon juice or ascorbic acid color keeper to keep from turning brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sand dabs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar together in bowl (should look like pudding).
Add vanilla; gently stir.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat mixture until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Add nuts and blend all together.
Shape into a large ball.
Shape into small 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until light golden color (do not overbake, do not brown).
Remove from oven and allow to set for 1 minute.
Roll or shake hot cookies in confectioners sugar until coated.
Cookies may be stored up to 6 weeks in cookie tins or container (cool storage). Recipe makes 40 to 45 (1-inch) ball cookies.

title: ralph's famous peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Take your 2 slices of bread.
Spread peanut butter on one side and jelly on the other side.
Serve with a cold glass of milk.

title: onion pie
directions: Make crust of crushed saltines and melted butter.
Saute onions, put on top of cracker crust.
Sprinkle on top of onions, cheese.
Add scalded milk, beaten eggs, salt, pepper and pour over onion cheese layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour or until set.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine cocoa and food color.
Cream together the butter, oil and sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
Mix in the cocoa and food coloring mixture.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to cocoa mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in the vinegar and the vanilla.
Pour into two baking dishes.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: good turkey
directions: Put turkey on rack in roaster. Add 3 cups water and vegetables. Preheat oven to 450°. Put turkey in oven and cook at 6 minutes per pound at 450°. Turn oven off, but leave turkey in. Cook late at night and leave in oven until morning. Your have juicy, tender turkey and lots of good broth.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Mix well until blended.
Spoon into ovenproof baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or crackers.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan on hot stove.
When water is hot, add cream of tartar.
When this begins to boil, break soda crackers into fourths and drop into the water.
Gently push under for about 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
It will seem thin, but will thicken as it bakes.
Cover generously with butter and cinnamon.
Place top crust on and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: weight watchers creamed chicken
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thick.
Serve over 1 serving of toasted bread.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Lightly skillet-brown chops and set aside.
Line bottom of shallow baking pan, large enough to add chops so they will lie flat, with raw rice.
Top with chops.
Top each chop with large onion slice, then large, unpeeled lemon slice.
Add undiluted consomme.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° until consomme is absorbed and chops and rice are done, approximately 1 hour. Discard lemons.
Mix onions and rice and serve as side dish with chops.

title: homemade caramel
directions: Melt margarine in a quart saucepan.
Add sugar and cream, then bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Boil, stirring constantly, for about 10 to 15 minutes, until mixture well thickens on spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and serve.

title: yum-yum
directions: Boil green peppers, onion and celery in a small amount of water, until tender.
Brown meat in skillet, separating into particles.
Remove surplus fat as it accumulates.
Add mushroom soup and half the chow mein noodles. Add vegetables; mix.
Add remaining noodles to top of skillet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mildred's jelly roll
directions: Cook on waxed paper in a 12 x 20-inch sheet pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, roll out on a wet cloth with a little sugar.
Fill with your favorite jelly.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Mix all well and place in ovensafe dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Crumble soda crackers on top and heat until crackers are brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and 2 cups of flour.
Press into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add 2 cups sugar, lemon juice, 1 tablespoon flour, baking powder and nuts.
Pour over pastry.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Dust with additional powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine orange juice, lemonade, sugar and egg.
Boil.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and fold in whipped topping.
Serve with fruit.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery and bouillon cubes in water and salt.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender.
Add 1 cup of milk.
Put in remaining milk and flour.
Stir until smooth and add to potatoes. Cook until thickened.
The dill really does liven this up.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together oats and boiling water; set aside.
Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add oat mixture; blend well.
Pour into nonstick sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread topping on cake; allow to cool.
Spread topping over cooled cake.

title: pork cordon bleu
directions: Place one ham slice over each pork chop.
Place on grill, low or medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour, turn every 10 minutes. After meat is tender, place 1/2 slice of cheese on top of each meat roll.
Continue cooking just long enough to begin melting cheese. Do not brown cheese.
Place on plate.
Pour 1/4 cup brandy over meat.
Light with long match just before serving.
If desired, serve on a bed of white or wild rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in lrg. bowl all the ingredients.
Pour into a 13 by 9 greased pan and bake for 45 min.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook livers, gizzards, onions and celery with chicken.
Mix and add enough chicken broth to make dressing soupy.
Place into a baking dish that has been sprayed with vegetable oil.
Cover and cook 30 minutes at 350° then uncover and cook 1 hour.

title: crab salad
directions: Cut Crab Delights in halves and combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least one hour before serving.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Cool cake and spread fudge topping over the top. Cool completely.
Mix 4 tablespoons creme de menthe in Cool Whip, which has been thawed in refrigerator.
Spread on cake. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: delicious chicken pie
directions: Put chicken on the bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Chip boiled eggs over this.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken and eggs. Mix 1 1/2 sticks of butter (melted), 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour.
Pour over top of pie and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Whip pudding with milk.
Let stand for a few minutes to thicken, then fold in Cool Whip.
Butter bottom of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Next, place whole crackers on bottom, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat, ending with a layer of crackers.

title: apple butter
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together and bake in a slow oven at 325° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add nutmeg, allspice and cinnamon.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour more.

title: cranberry orange oat bread
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, orange rind, orange juice and oil; add to flour mixture and mix just enough to moisten flour.
Stir in cereal, cranberries and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.
Makes 18 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas and soak for 1 hour.
Place meat, water, peas, salt and whole onion in a large pot.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove onion; add okra and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until okra is done.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Combine all.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: irene's low-cal dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a jar and store in refrigerator. Shake well when ready to use.
If too sour, add a little sugar substitute.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend sour cream and sugar with 1 stick butter, melted.
Stir into yeast mixture with eggs, flour and salt.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise, covered, until double in bulk.
Divide into 4 portions. Roll each into a 12-inch circle.
Brush each with 2 tablespoons of butter; cut each into 12 wedges.
Roll up from wide end, shaping into crescents.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until browned.
Rolls may be frozen after shaping into crescents.

title: sally lunn
directions: Scald the milk, add to the butter and let stand to lukewarm. Add yeast, salt, sugar and flour.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Cover and let stand in a warm place for 2 hours or until very light.
Beat egg whites then yolks.
Add yolks and then whites.
Stir in carefully.
Let stand in warm place for 15 minutes, then turn into a greased Turk's head.
Bake in moderate oven for 40 minutes.

title: garlic-cheese bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut bread lengthwise in half. On cookie sheet, broil 1 to 2
minutes until lightly browned.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over bread.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Cut bread crosswise into strips.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Put peanut butter on 1 piece of bread, then get the jelly and spread it on the other piece of bread, then you put each piece together and mash it.

title: aunt margaret's corn dish
directions: Stir together ingredients. Bake at 350° in 2-quart greased casserole dish for 45 minutes.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice with all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix at low speed 30 seconds until well mixed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Drizzle remaining orange juice over warm cake.
Sprinkle with sugar nut topping composed of 1/3 cup sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: peanut butter chocolate muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir in the cocoa and sugar. In a medium bowl, beat the peanut butter, melted butter, egg, and vanilla extract until the mixture is smooth. Pour the peanut butter mixture and

the chocolate chips into the flour mixture. Stir until blended. The batter will be stiff. Fill greased muffin tins full. Bake for 20 minutes or until a tester inserted in a muffin comes out clean. Makes one dozen muffins.

title: shrimp spread for sandwiches
directions: Let cream cheese get room temperature; add lemon juice, onion, pepper and celery. Chop shrimp in food processor and add to cream cheese mixture. Add mayonnaise. Chill. Serve with crackers or spread on little rounds of bread.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk; add remaining ingredients, except for chili sauce.
Mix well.
Pack into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan to shape.
Invert on shallow baking pan.
Score loaf diagonally with handle of wooden spoon.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Fill scored marks on top with chili sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: russian chicken
directions: Season chicken and set aside.
Mix ingredients in a bowl. Spread mixture over chicken parts in large baking pan.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove, cover and continue baking until juice has been absorbed, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Pat in a 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: green chile roll ups
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into 8 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Combine cream cheese and remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over rectangles.
Roll up rectangles, starting at long side; pinch seams to seal.
Cut each roll into 10 slices; place slices, cut side down, on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.

title: tennessee country ham
directions: Soak ham in 50 pound lard can filled with cold water overnight.
Pour off water; put rack in bottom of lard stand. Place ham in cloth sack; put on rack in can.
Fill with cold water to within 2-inches of the top.
Put top on securely.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 40 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Place can on a stack of 5 or 6 large magazines.
Wrap can with several layers of newspaper and tie with a string.
Then wrap 2 or 3 quilts or heavy coats to keep heat in.
Let it stay wrapped in a cool place for 24 hours.
Unwrap and remove ham from hot water.
Chill and slice.

title: oven stewed rabbit
directions: Put rabbit in a layer in a medium roaster.
Put water, cubes, bay leaves and pepper in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve cubes.
Sprinkle raw cut up vegetables over rabbit in roaster.
Pour hot broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine over medium-low heat. Add onion and brown sugar.
Cook until a golden yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on high heat until steaming, then reduce to low heat for 25 to 30 minutes (sometimes takes longer).
Serves 4.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butter in the pan and add the following:
crumbs, coconut, chocolate bits and nuts.
Pour the milk over everything.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into small pieces.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scald milk and butter.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stirring together, gradually add milk and butter to the egg mixture.
Beat together until foam forms on top. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and cook 20 minutes or more until firm.
Cool and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and Karo.	Mix well and add salt, vanilla and the melted butter.
Place pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell.	Pour filling over pecans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; season to taste.
Mix all canned products and ground meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Break up chocolate bars.
Place in large bowl.
Add boiling water to cover chocolate and place dish towel on top of bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Whip egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Whip the cream.
Pour off water.
Chocolate should be melted.
Add yolks of 6 eggs and 1/4 tablespoon sugar and mix well.
Fold in whipping cream, which has been "whipped" in Mixmaster.
Then fold in egg whites, which have been beaten until they're stiff but not dry.
Pour mousse into bowl.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours. Decorate with more whipped cream.
Serves approximately 8 people.

title: baked potato salad
directions: After potatoes are chilled, grate.
Add onion and sour cream. Heat cheese, milk and butter.
Add to potato mixture and blend thoroughly with spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Put in an 8 1/2 x 13-inch oblong baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Place warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Make sure the water is not hot since this will kill the yeast.
Add the yeast, sugar, and oil to the water. Slowly mix in flour one cup at a time until the dough begins to get difficult to stir.
Now add the salt. Sugar helps yeast activate while salt slows the activation so it is best to add the salt last.
Continue adding flour as you begin kneading the dough by hand.
Knead for approximately 8 - 10 minutes being sure not to add too much flour.
The dough should be soft and spongy when done.
Set the dough in a slightly warmed (but off) oven until doubled in size.
Pan rolls out by taking 24 even sized hand fulls of dough and making 3 X 5 rectangles on a table.
Place 8 slices (small) in two rows on each roll.
Roll up. Place on greased sheet.
Let rise again till doubled in size. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Brush with butter at the 20 minute time limit.
These may be served plain or sliced with cheese and sauce added.
Yield - 2 dozen rolls.

title: cavatini
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Brown onion and hamburger.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 c. cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Add cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: ragin' cajun casserole
directions: Saut smoked sausage in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes or until browned. Add onion and next 3 ingredients. Saut 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomatoes and next 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil and stir in rice. Cover. Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Stir in shrimp. Cook 3 to 5 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink. Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon rice casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, layer all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: fried yam sticks
directions: Boil or bake yam until tender; do not overcook.
Let yam cool. Peel and discard skin.
Cut potato in sticks like French fries. Heat oil and margarine until hot in skillet.
Add potato sticks. Fry on medium until crispy.
Turn frequently; sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: pig cake icing
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and mix liquid with pudding.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix eggs and milk together, then mix with cake mixture.
Add peaches and bake at 350° until done.

title: cadie pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Add marshmallows while hot to melt them.
Cool in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.
Whip cream and add to mixture.
Put in a casserole dish in layers as follows:
graham cracker crumbs, pineapple and whipped cream mixture until all is used.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: czechoslovakian jam bars(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Set oven at 350° (moderate).
Line 8-inch square pan with waxed paper.
Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks and beat well, then add flour slowly.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon half of batter into 8-inch square cake pan, spreading evenly to corners. Top with strawberry jam, stopping about 1 inch from edge of batter on all sides.
Cover with remaining cookie dough.
If dough sticks to spoon while spreading, dip spoon in cold water.
Bake 1 hour or until light brown.
Cool.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch bars.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chili powder, and shape into logs. Roll logs in chili powder to coat.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. Cut thin slices and serve on crackers.
Will keep in the refrigerator indefinitely.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla extract, salt and pecans in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is melted and well blended.
Fill each shell half full with filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 15.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients into crock-pot in the order listed. Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; add condensed milk and beat.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise and beat again.
Add salt, cheese, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole type dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Prepare pastry shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown hamburger meat in skillet with onions and green pepper, then drain off any excess fat.
Reserve a small amount and place remaining meat mixture in pastry shell.
Sprinkle cheeses over meat.
Beat eggs, cream and seasonings and pour over meat and cheeses.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer, or until firm.
Sprinkle remaining meat on top and bake 5 more minutes.
Let pie stand 10 minutes before serving.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix, using directions on box, except use 2 whole eggs rather than just the whites.
Bake two 9-inch layers and split in half.

title: cheese popover puffs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Heat a well-greased muffin pan at 425° for 3 minutes or until very hot. Spoon in batter, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately.
Yields 8 popovers.

title: baked round steak
directions: Cover steak with sauerkraut, mushrooms and green pepper. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up, using toothpicks to hold.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Slice as cinnamon roll to serve.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all liquids first; heat.
Add cooked pork and beef to the veggies and liquids.
Allow this to simmer for several hours. Add more chicken broth if stew becomes too thick.
Put the potatoes in last and when everything is well cooked, add the chicken and allow it to heat again.
Serve on rice.
Enjoy. Serves 40.

title: fat-free vegie stir-fry
directions: Coat large skillet or wok with cooking spray, heat (skillet or wok) on medium heat until hot.
Add all ingredients; stir-fry about 5 minutes or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Yields 4 servings (about 38 calories per serving, no fat).
Any vegetable can be added for variety.

title: gertrude's brown bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 1 minute.
I use a No. 5 iron skillet (which, of course, is never really washed!) and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry wine jelly
directions: Combine sugar, cranberry juice, cinnamon and cloves in Dutch oven.
If using cranberries, crush in blender and add them too. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in wine and pectin.
Skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour jelly into sterilized jelly jars (to hold 7 cups), leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with 1/8 inch of melted paraffin.
Cover with lids.

title: grandma nettie cannon's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Grind cinnamon pieces.
Bring all ingredients to a boil; cook for 40 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Press down on bottom of pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°. Cool thoroughly.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, 2 sticks soft oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla for 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas lengthwise and place on top of mixture. Drain can of crushed pineapple and place over bananas.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans.
Garnish with cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and whipped cream, eggs and salt in a bowl, mix thoroughly.
Add condensed milk and dairy milk; pour into ice cream maker.
Follow directions.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with ingredients.
Refill whites and top with paprika if desired.

title: fresh garden fry
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix 1 cup flour or corn meal.
Mix well and fry in skillet with 1/4 cup oil (may have to add more oil).
Cook until done.

title: crispy pretzel bars
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, combine the sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on high for 3 minutes until sugar is dissolved. (you can do this part on the stove also). Stir in peanut butter until blended. Add the cereal, pretzel and M&M's, stir until coated. Press into a greased cake pan. Cut into bars.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix altogether and serve with different fruit.
Very good!

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper in diet margarine until tender.
Stir in condensed soup, mushrooms, pimento, skim milk and basil.
Lay half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with half each of soup mixture, cottage cheese, American cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers of the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining American and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 2 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 10.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together meal, salt, and sugar.
Put butter into water and let boil.
Then put eggs and milk into mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 400 degrees.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients in mixer until smooth.
Add to meat mixture.
Simmer for 45 minutes (watch for sticking).

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light.
Add unbeaten eggs and blend.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes until lightly browned. Makes 4 dozen.

title: texas cream fudge
directions: Boil sugar, brown sugar, Carnation milk and Karo until soft ball stage reached.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly and beat until creamy colored and thickened.
Add pecans and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Beat eggs, Bisquick, oleo, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add broccoli.
Pour into 9-inch pie dish.
Top with bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: seven layer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in a clear 2 quart bowl.
(It is pretty in a pedestal bowl).
In a separate bowl, blend cream cheese, lemon juice and lemon rind. Set aside.
Whip cream to soft stage. Gradually add sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold sweetened whipped cream into cream cheese mixture and spread over the layered fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add maraschino cherries, if desired.
Keep chilled.

title: grandma's glazed apples
directions: Boil all ingredients for 5 minutes, except apples.
Add apples and cook slowly until tender.
Put apples in a flat pan and sprinkle with sugar; place in oven a few minutes to glaze.

title: never fail coconut pie
directions: Pie:
Mix flour and sugar together in double boiler; add a little milk to make a paste to prevent lumps.
Stir and add rest of milk.
Cook a few minutes until bubbly.
Beat egg yolks in separate bowl; stir a little milk mixture into yolks, then pour into milk mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir in pack of coconut (hold back a little coconut to sprinkle over top) and pour into baked pie crust.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greeting and smiles; then add handshakes beaten separately.
Add love slowly.
Sift sympathy and hospitality, fold in carefully.
Bake in a moderately warm oven of even temperature.
This serves an indefinite number and never becomes stale.

title: dot's favorite potato salad
directions: Lightly toss potatoes, celery, hard boiled eggs, and onion together in a bowl.
Fry bacon in a heavy skillet until pieces are browned.
Stir a mixture of salt, pepper, dry mustard, and sugar into the vinegar and water.
Add to the beaten eggs and mix well. Pour egg mixture into the hot bacon and fat and stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Pour over the potato mixture and toss lightly to mix thoroughly.
Chill 3 - 4 hours or overnight.

title: super fast chili
directions: Brown ground beef and diced onion, drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and cook until boiling.
Simmer until served.

title: plain tea cakes
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Roll out and cut out or make little balls and flatten with a glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cake will not brown, but will be crisp when cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss together and put in casserole.
Pour 1 can cream of chicken soup over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole and top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 275° or 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: adam's chocolate chip dessert
directions: *Whatever your Mom doesn't use when she's making pies.
Try to get her to make extra.

title: drunk shrimp
directions: Cook fresh shrimp, peeled, in olive oil over high heat until shrimp are pink.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts. Pour in a greased baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done; cool.
Combine frosting ingredients.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Heat milk in double boiler or set pan in water and let milk come almost to the boiling point.
Beat eggs and mix with sugar, salt, flour and 1 cup of milk.
Add this to hot milk and stir until it is thickness you want.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add vanilla after cooking. Serve cold.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, peanut butter, baking soda and salt (combining dry ingredients first). Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely and frost.

title: microwave ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and rinse.
Place peas in a 2 1/2-quart microwave casserole.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cooked noodles. Mix lightly.
Cover; microwave 9 to 10 minutes, until heated through, stirring once.

title: egg sauce
directions: In a large 4 quart saucepan, melt a pound of butter or oleo over medium high heat.
While heat is still on, whisk in a little at a time about 3 pounds of flour.
Beat it hard every time (no lumps).
It will be real thick.
When cooled, shave it off with large spoon (takes less whipping to thicken all gravies and sauces.)

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add scalded milk.
Stir together until dissolved.
Beat egg yolks in bowl.
Gradually pour 1 cup of hot milk mixture into eggs while beating.
Return egg mixture back to milk mixture.
Bring all to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and evaporated milk. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into milk and egg mixture. Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Add the 4 cups of cold milk.
Freeze according to your freezer instructions.

title: pickled carrots(wanda's)
directions: Mix together and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool and pour over cooked carrots.

title: hot dip
directions: Blend in blender.
Do not oil.
Add two tablespoons Wesson oil and heat.

title: pancake pizza
directions: Place Bisquick in bowl.
Combine the eggs, milk, oil and syrup; add to biscuit mix and mix well.
Spread onto greased 14 inch pizza pan; sprinkle with granola and nuts.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into wedges. Serve with additional syrup.
Serves 8.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together soda, salt and flour and add alternately with buttermilk to butter mixture.
Add grated orange rind and vanilla.
Blend together 1/2 cup flour, dates and pecans and add to mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish.
Put extra cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mama's pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover in a large bowl.
Store in refrigerator at least overnight before serving.

title: pab's preconcert spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add garlic and red pepper.
Add tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Boil spaghetti and broccoli until desired consistency and drain.
Toss sauce, spaghetti and broccoli.
Add cheese.

title: cheese ball spread
directions: Blend cheeses with half of nuts and parsley flakes and form into a ball.
Freeze for 1/2 hour.
Remove from freezer.
Roll into ball the remaining nuts and parsley flakes.
Put back in refrigerator.
May be made 3 or 4 days ahead of time.
Serves 12.

title: morning coffee cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Mix together well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter evenly over top; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best eaten when still warm.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and Swiss all-purpose buttermilk. Gradually beat in water until smooth.
Set aside.

title: homemade french fries
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in french fry style. Pour milk and egg in a large bowl. Mix well. Add potatoes. Stir with hands to cover potatoes with egg and milk mixture. Sprinkle with flour to cover potatoes. Fry in vegetable oil.

title: wilma's karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup, salt, sugar mixed with flour, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in half the corn flake crumbs, then sprinkle rest on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press into buttered 8-inch pie pan, building up the sides.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Wash zucchini and slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Cook onion in margarine and then add the zucchini slices.
Cook for 5 minutes slowly, turning zucchini slices so they will cook on both sides. Add sliced tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle cheese on top and simmer just until cheese melts.

title: fish fillets in foil #2
directions: Will also need four 12-inch pieces of foil.

title: sourdough hot cakes
directions: Beat egg yolks with salt until thick and light.
Stir in 2 cups of sourdough starter.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Fold gently into first mixture.
Dissolve soda in 2 teaspoons water; carefully add to batter.
Bake pancakes on hot, buttered griddle, turning once.
When ready to be turned, tops of pancakes will still be wet and bubbles won't be so firm as in ordinary pancakes.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soups, chilies and heat.
Dip tortillas in mixture and layer tortillas, ground meat and grated cheese in casserole. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apricot cobble up
directions: Combine first three ingredients; stir in butter until evenly distributed. Add milk, and mix well. Spread batter in a greased 8 inch square baking pan. Drain apricots, reserving syrup. Arrange apricot halves, cut side down, on top of batter; pour syrup over top. Bake at 400° for 30-35 minutes. Serve warm with cream.

title: easy fried donuts
directions: Prepare biscuits by cutting or making hole in center.
Drop in preheated deep fryer or pan fairly deep in oil.
Cook until brown. Drain on paper towel.
Dip in powdered sugar icing made with powdered sugar and small amount of milk.
Eat.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook macaroni until almost done.
Mix sauce, beef and macaroni.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan; add a layer of pepperoni (save a few slices for top).
Then add the rest of the macaroni mixture.
Top with cheese and pepperoni. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: quick strawberry dessert
directions: Put some strawberries in a bowl.
Add some Cool Whip and mix well.
Add some nuts (I use pecans, chopped).

title: heavenly divinity salad
directions: Place Cool Whip in a large bowl and stir well to fluff up. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together with diced onion and catsup to taste.
Heat in skillet until well mixed and onion is tender.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until blended in.
Combine salt with flour and add to sugar mixture, alternating with the milk, ending with flour.
Add lemon extract; blend.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven; let sit for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: easy make brunch casserole
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add all remaining ingredients except diced chilies.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chilies.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until puffy and brown.
May be served hot or cold.
May be made night before and refrigerated (covered with wrap or foil).
Set out 10 minutes before baking.
Serve with salsa sauce on the side. This is a good recipe for camping, too.
Use a heavy covered Dutch oven to bake over fire.
Cut recipe in half for smaller group.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Remove orange sections and chop.
Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in
a greased baking dish and top with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost or eat plain.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Make everything but pecans into a ball and roll in the pecan pieces.
Serve with party crackers.

title: vegetable and fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Stays fresh for several days or can mix dressing ingredients and add right before serving.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto bottom of jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package directions.

title: pineapple refrigerated dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 13-inch pans. Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Divide mixture into the pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cucumber sour cream mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin and salt in large bowl at least 2 minutes, until completely dissolved. Stir in cold water and lemon juice. Refrigerate about 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened. Mix salad dressing and sour cream in small bowl until well blended. Stir in thickened gelatin. Refrigerate about 15 minutes or until thickened. Stir in cucumbers, onion and dill weed. Pour into 5-cup mold. REFRIGERATE 4 hours or until firm. Unmold.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift in all dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet until delicately browned.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: oxtail bean soup
directions: Place oxtail, salt and pepper in pan with water and boil until meat falls off bone, adding water as needed.

title: mexican squash
directions: Add 1 cup water, bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 10-12 minutes until squash is tender. Serve over white rice.

title: cheesy burger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring, until crumbly; drain. Saute green pepper and green onions with garlic salt in margarine in skillet until tender.
Mix in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thick.
Stir in soup.
Simmer for several minutes.
Add ground beef and cheese, mixing well.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Mix in celery, salt and pepper.
Combine with spaghetti in baking dish, mixing well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: angel strawberry delight
directions: In large casserole dish, crumble angel food cake.
Prepare instant pudding as indicated on box.
Pour layer on top of cake; add layer of strawberries; then layer of Cool Whip.
Strawberries can be put on top, if desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well and pour into a casserole.
Add a piece of butter to the top.
Place into a pan of 1-inch boiling water at 350° for 40 minutes.
Place a knife through the center.
Draw the knife out. If any corn is on the knife, let bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Cook celery, onion and carrots in tomato sauce and diced tomatoes until tender.
(I use microwave 15 to 20 minutes.)
Add squash and zucchini.
Cook until tender.
Don't overcook zucchini and squash.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and cover with foil and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Drain juice.
Combine in saucepan stewed tomatoes, sauce, oregano, flour and cheese and cook until sauce fairly thickens.
Pour over chicken and bake 10 minutes uncovered. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; drain.
To veggies, add sour cream, soup, 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remainder of onion rings.
Bake additional 5 minutes.

title: supreme chicken roulades
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and bouillon.
Remove from heat.
Drain mushroom liquid into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 2 cups.
Gradually stir mushroom liquid and milk into margarine/flour mixture.
Place over medium heat; stir constantly until sauce thickens and boils.
Add mushrooms.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Spread mixture evenly in greased 8-inch square pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 minutes or until brown. Cool on cake rack.

title: minestrone(italian soup)
directions: Heat 6 cups of water to boiling in a large saucepan. Gradually add navy beans to boiling water.
Simmer 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Set aside to soak, about 1 hour.
Add salt pork to beans.
Return to heat and simmer one hour.

title: southern italian potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes and add salt to taste; boil until done.
Drain potatoes.
Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons Italian dressing over the potatoes while hot (low calorie is good).
Add 1/2 onion, 1/2 bell pepper, 2 stems celery and 2 tablespoons sweet pickle chips. Stir these ingredients together. Add 1/2 teaspoon mustard and 4 or 5 tablespoons mayonnaise.
(Be sure the ingredients are chopped fine.)
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with green olives.

title: easy homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine condensed milk and chocolate milk.
Mix thoroughly into one gallon ice cream freezer and freeze like any other homemade ice cream.

title: tomato rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole.
Cook 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Before cooked, add 1/2 cup cream.

title: play dough
directions: No need to worry when it comes to tomatoes, as tomato sauce can be substituted for a host of other tomato products.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender making sure all of the water is gone. Add mushroom soup, onion, cheese and top with chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and chicken breast.
Heat up cream of mushroom soup.
Tear tortillas (approximately 1-inch squares).

title: orange sticks
directions: Peel orange in quarters and cut in narrow strips.
Place peels in saucepan.
Cover in cold water and let it boil up once and drain; repeat 5 times.
Heat the sugar with hot water.
When dissolved, add orange peel.
Cook slowly until syrup is nearly evaporated; drain and roll the strips in sugar.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to hold together.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package. Pour 1/2 of batter in a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake only 15 minutes.
In a double boiler or microwave, melt caramels with milk and butter.
Pour this over baked portion of cake.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining cake batter over nut and chip layer.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not use smaller pan.

title: smoren(pancake crumble)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Beat with whisk.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in frying pan.
Add batter; let cook for 1 minute, then flip and chop into pieces with spatula.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream with taco sauce.
Spread over meat mixture.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Dip chips while hot.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix and melt everything except potatoes.
Put potatoes in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Pour melted mixture over potatoes.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a bowl, stir together the oats, wheat germ and sunflower seeds.
In a small saucepan, heat, stirring until hot, then remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oat mixture until combined well.
Spread granola evenly in bottom of a jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) and bake in middle of oven, stirring occasionally.
Cook 40 minutes or until golden.
Cool granola and stir in raisins and nuts.
Granola can be kept in an airtight container, chilled. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: shrimp-e-doos
directions: Halve and quarter the English muffins.
Blend together all the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze.
After they are frozen, bag and store. Bake as needed at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: eileen's dessert
directions: Mix together and form ball of dough ingredients.
Pat into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: weight watcher's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour dressing over top. Mix well.

title: edible dirt
directions: Mix
pudding
according
to package directions, using 1 cup less milk.
Let set for a few minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, margarine
and
powdered
sugar;
add to pudding mix. Line a medium size flowerpot with foil or Saran Wrap.
Place a layer
of pudding
mix in flowerpot, then cookies.
Alternate layers, ending
with
cookies.
Place an artificial flower in the
center of
the
pot
and
gummy worms on top of cookies. Serve by spoonful.
This is delicious and a lot of fun.

title: bacon fat cookies
directions: Mix sugar and bacon fat together.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Shape into rolls and wrap in wax paper. Chill.
Cut into thin slices; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scandinavian apple cake
directions: Jelly-glazed apple or plum slices top this sour cream pound cake that bakes to pastry shop perfection.

title: all-american meatballs(microwave cooking)
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, soup mix, parsley flakes and egg in large bowl.
Shape into 12 (1 1/2-inch) meatballs.
Set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix beef broth and Worcestershire sauce. Add meatballs.
Cook covered on 70% Power (Roast) for 10 minutes. Combine cornstarch and water in small bowl until smooth.
Stir into meatballs and cover.
Cook on 70% Power (Roast) for 3 to 4 minutes or until sauce is thickened (200° if using probe).
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix in order given.
Top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: cough syrup
directions: Mix equal portions of glycerine, lemon juice, honey and olive oil.
Shake well before using.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple slices, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Cut pineapple slices into quarters, set pineapple and juice aside.
On waxed paper, mix flour and salt; use to coat chicken breasts.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken breasts until golden and fork-tender, about 10 minutes, turning once.
Remove the chicken breasts to a warm platter; keep warm. Into drippings in skillet stir honey, teriyaki sauce, dried chives, pepper and reserved pineapple juice.
Over high heat, heat to boiling; boil 30 seconds.
Add pineapple; heat through.
Pour sauce over chicken; garnish with fresh chives.
Serves 4.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; reserve 1/2 cup cheese for top.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Stir and cook 6 more minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix meat, sauce, milk and soup mix.
Shape into approximately 20 balls and brown in broiler.
Do not turn.
Do not overcook.

title: 1950's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
With a study spoon, mix in slowly the sugar, chips, flour, vanilla and pecans, one ingredient at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Flatten with a greased and sugared glass bottom to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: mound cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding.
Add eggs, oil and water.
Mix together and beat well.
Bake as directed on package in well-greased pan.
Remove from oven.
Cool in pan.
After cooling, make holes in cake (handle of wooden spoon may be used).
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle can of coconut over top.
Refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo, add egg and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into mixture.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out small amounts at a time.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: raisin jumbles
directions: Simmer raisins in 1 cup water until tender and plump.
Drain liquid off raisins into measuring cup; add water to make 1 1/2 cups.

title: beet pickles
directions: Pare, slice and cook beets.
Place in jars.
Make pickling syrup by combining rest of ingredients.
Put cinnamon, cloves and allspice in a bag.
Bring syrup to a boil and simmer a few minutes to allow spices to be absorbed.
Pour hot syrup over beets.
Seal.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash and skin chicken breasts.	Beat Ritz crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix melted margarine with cracker crumbs.	Salt and pepper
chicken; roll chicken in cracker crumbs.
Bake in heavy tinfoil for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana-orange-dairy delight
directions: Blend banana in blender with 2 tablespoons frozen orange juice.
Add 1 cup milk.
Blend for 1 minute.
Enjoy!

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Mix soup, tomatoes and onions.
Add chicken and mix.
Cut 1/2 of the cheese in bite size pieces.
Add and mix.
Spray 9 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with chicken mixture.
Slice rest of cheese and put on top of mixture.
Cover all with 3/4 bag crushed Doritos.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can use leftover turkey.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and heat in saucepan until sugar melts.
Pour over chicken, pork or beef and cook as usual in oven.
May be used as a marinade and/or barbecue sauce in oven or on grill.
Kids love it.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix these 5 ingredients lightly.
Serve chilled.

title: oriental vinaigrette
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 tablespoon of water.
Stir well and set aside.

title: oven baked steak
directions: Cut steak into serving portions; brown on both sides in oil in skillet and transfer to roasting pan. Brown onion lightly in skillet. Combine remaining ingredients for barbecue sauce; add onions and simmer for 5
minutes. Pour sauce over steak; cover and bake 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish, then cheese and then sausage.
Sprinkle these evenly over the bread.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over the bread, sausage and cheese.* Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red, white and purple eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant, do not peel.
Trim stems; cut in 1/4 to 3/8 inch slices. Salt eggplant and drain for 30 minutes.
Heat 1 or 2 tablespoons oil and saute onions on low for 10 minutes in nonstick skillet.
Remove from pan; pat eggplant dry.
Brown in remaining oil; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spray Mazola lightly on 9 x 6-inch (2-quart) dish.
Start layering with 1/2 of the onions, 1/2 tablespoon basil, 1/2 of tomatoes, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of hot sauce and repeat the process.
Cover dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Lightly oil a griddle and heat to 325° or medium heat.
Ladle the potato mixture onto the griddle, slightly flatten.
Cook about 8 to 10 minutes on one side, then turn and cook for 5 to 8 minutes more.

title: coconut pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine pumpkin, milk, 1/2 cup water, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Remove from boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add rest of sugar.
Beat until stiff. Fold in pumpkin, vanilla and 3/4 of the toasted coconut.
Turn in cold pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
To serve, top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Combine blueberries, 2/3 cup sugar, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water.
In medium saucepan, cook over low heat until berries are soft.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in small jar.
Shake until dissolved.
Add cornstarch mixture to blueberry mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in a small bowl; mix well.
Press evenly into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and 2/3 cup sugar. Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread mixture evenly over cooled crust.
Pour blueberry mixture evenly over all. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in pan (for 9 x 13-inch, double the ingredients).
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
(It tastes like dressing.)

title: talk of the town pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour;
add margarine and eggs, mixing well. Add other ingredients.
Bake
in
unbaked crust at 300° about 1 hour, or until done.

title: pasta
directions: Brown hamburger meat on medium-high or slow.
Add 1/2 onion and 1/2 bell pepper; cook for 5 minutes.
