Pour grease from pan. Add Hunt's sauce with mushrooms, pepper, garlic salt and cheese. Stir well to taste.
Cover well on low heat and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Boil noodles on medium-high for 10 minutes or until they are tender.
Strain noodles.
Combine with sauce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix balance of ingredients and pour over crust which has been baked.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: fruit fritters
directions: Separate egg yolks from egg whites and beat the whites until stiff.
Add first 5 ingredients to the egg yolks in order.
Beat until smooth.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Dust fruit with flour and dip into batter.
Fry in an inch of hot oil about 5 minutes.
Remove from oil.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: grandmother's corn bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased pan and bake in oven for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti pasta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti according to directions on box.
Dice tomatoes, bell pepper, onion and crab meat.
In bowl, toss all ingredients together, mixing well.
Allow to refrigerate for at least 2 hours (can be prepared up to 2 days in advance before serving).
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Add more Zesty Italian dressing, if needed and if salad has set for more than 2 days.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In 1-quart bowl (not aluminum), sprinkle chicken with cornstarch, tossing to coat.
Add sherry and soy sauce and stir to combine.
Let mixture marinate for 15 minutes.
In 8 or 9-inch nonstick skillet, heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer several chicken cubes to skillet, allowing marinade that adheres to chicken to drip into bowl.
Cook chicken, stirring quickly and frequently until browned.
Remove from skillet and repeat with remaining chicken, reserving marinade left in bowl.
In same skillet, heat remaining oil; add onion and cashews and stir-fry until onion is translucent.
Add pepper, mushrooms and garlic; stir-fry one minute.
Return chicken to skillet; add water chestnuts, reserved liquid, hoisin sauce and reserved marinade and stir until combined.
Cover and cook until chicken is cooked through and sauce thickens, 1 to 2 minutes. Serve sprinkled with scallion.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: kringle(pastry)
directions: Mix 1/2 cup margarine, 1 cup flour and 1 tablespoon water. Put out on cookie sheet in 2 strips, about 3 x 12-inches.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until smooth.
Fold in chocolates.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cake tester inserted in center should come out clean. Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out on wire rack to finish cooling.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: venison meat dish
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix in bottom of baking dish.
Shape venison and sausage in loaf after mixing together.
Place in baking dish.
Pour cream of celery soup over mixture with small amount of water.
Cover and bake at 350° until done.

title: apple rings
directions: Blend both sugar and margarine in long baking dish.
Place in 400° oven until mixture boils.

title: szechuan broccoli
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl; set aside.
Heat a large skillet over medium heat.
Add sesame seed. Cook 1 minute, until browned.
Set aside.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add soy sauce mixture; stir well.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Contains 72 calories and 3.6 fat per 1 cup serving.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Blend together flour, egg yolk, brown sugar, softened butter and vanilla. Pat into cookie sheet. Bake on buttered cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden. While baking, melt chocolate bar in top of double boiler. Remove cookies and while hot spread with melted chocolate and sprinkle on pecans. Cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add milk, eggs and vegetable oil.
Add salt, poppy seed filling and vanilla.
Spoon into muffin cups about 1/4 full.
Then add one-third teaspoon of lemon filling,
then cover and add to about two-thirds full with more batter.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, being careful not to overbake.
Remove from oven.
Need not be iced.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt cubes of almond bark in a double boiler.
Stir in peanut butter until just dissolved.
As it cools, stir in Rice Krispies. Pour in Pam sprayed 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cut into squares before it hardens.
Store in refrigerator.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In bowl, mix soup, milk, onion and mustard until blended.
In greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread drained sauerkraut; top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon or pour soup mix evenly over noodles.
Sprinkle with corned beef, then layer with cheese.
In a separate bowl, stir together rye bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over top of cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Serves 8 to 10. Enjoy!

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter; pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix the rest of the ingredients and put on top of the other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups and place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of pie filling and chill.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: jeanne's apple bread pudding
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon together; add eggs and soft margarine. Beat until creamy.
Alternately add milk and bread to mixture and stir until bread is smooth.
Then add chopped apples and raisins. Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake, uncovered, for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: tropical cheese spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and pineapple, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or French bread slices.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and put in bottom of casserole. Mix sugar, flour and cheese.
Sprinkle on top of pineapple. Melt butter. Crumble crackers and mix with butter. Spread on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salt and water to cover until nearly done (bay leaves and cloves are optional).
Remove chicken; debone and skin.
Place broccoli in buttered baking dish; top with chicken.
Mix together soup, margarine, chicken stock and curry powder.
Cover chicken with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender.

title: fresh strawberry pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix with oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add berries and gelatin.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 4 x 9-inch bread pans.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 2 1/2 minutes (soft ball stage). Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into greased pan and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in zucchini.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Beat into first mixture and fold in nutmeats.
Bake at 325° in 2 well-greased loaf pans for 60 to 75 minutes.
Test at 1 hour, then test each 5 minutes until wooden pick comes out clean and dry.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: In large bowl, sift flour with baking powder, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cut shortening into mixture.
Combine milk and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Peel apples; quarter and slice.
Spread batter into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices in a row or pattern on top of batter, pressing in lightly but not flat.
Sprinkle cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Mix all ingredients in roasting pan.
(You can mix all the liquid ingredients and spices and then pour over chicken, mushrooms, artichoke hearts and onion.)
Bake at 325°, uncovered, at least 1 1/2 hours, stirring a couple of times.
Serve over rice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing mix, in a baking dish.
Put stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix well.
Serves 48 (4 oz.) cups.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/4-inch slices and pare; soak for several minutes in salty water.
Dip eggplant slices into egg and roll in flour.
Fry until golden brown.
Place in layers in baking dish, with onions and cheese; season.
Pour in tomato sauce; cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring the first 7 ingredients to a boil and cook on low 20 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer, slowly, for 45 minutes.
Taste for seasoning.
This sauce freezes well.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; combine juice from pineapple with sugar. Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool slightly; add drained pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Let stand a few hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and place in buttered casserole dish.
Brown meat and add sauce.
Cover noodles with melted cream cheese and Pet milk, then cover with meat sauce.
Grate Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: grandma's skillet dinner(complete meal in a skillet)
directions: Scrub potatoes (do not peel) and slice about 1/8-inch thick. Salt and pepper lightly.
Put potatoes in pan or skillet with a cover.
Layer with slices of ham or Canadian bacon, then sliced apples.
Sprinkle apple layer lightly with brown sugar and add 4th layer with slices of ham; repeat layering process to top of skillet.
Add butter and water.
Cover and cook 1/2 to 3/4 hour on stove top burner (heat level depends on your stove).
Serve in skillet along with bread and butter.
Enjoy!

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in glass baking dish, 7 x 11-inch.
Drain the peaches; set aside.
Use juice and milk.
Whip with the egg, sugar, flour and instant pudding.
Pour this into baking pan, then arrange peach slices on top.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: Place the first 7 ingredients in pot and boil.
Skim off brown foam (from the beans) as it boils.
Season well with garlic, oregano, thyme, Italian seasonings, pepper and whatever you prefer to cook with.

title: irresistible low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In 2-quart glass measure with handle, combine milk, cocoa and chips.
Cook in microwave on 100% power (High) for 2 minutes or until chips melt.
Stir after each minute. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
One brownie equals 120 calories.

title: vivian's quick peach cobbler
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9 x 13 pan with pie crust. Drain 2 cans of peaches (leave syrup from 1 can to use in recipe.) Pour 2 cans of drained peaches and 1 can peaches with syrup in a large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients together then stir into peaches. Pour this mixture onto pie shell.
Dot with butter, cover with pie crust and bake at 375° until done.

title: portobello mushroom soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in the olive oil.
Add 2 tablespoons flour; stir until dissolved.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes until heated to "bubble."
Add about 1 ounce of sherry.
Serve immediately.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine and vanilla, mixing well until blended.
Add eggs.
Mix at low speed until blended. Gradually add flour, sifted with baking powder, mixing at low speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender and debone. Set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add a little oil and milk.
Add enough all-purpose flour to make stiff enough to handle (not too stiff). Roll out on self-rising flour, very thin.
Cut with round biscuit cutter.
Add to chicken broth that is simmering. Turn with fork when all dough has been used.
Add chicken or celery soup and canned milk. Simmer until done.
Add chicken along with dumplings.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Heat butter or oleo in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Layer 1/3 of the potatoes, 1/2 of the onion and ham and 1/3 of the white sauce in casserole; repeat.
Top with remaining potatoes and white sauce.
Dot with 1 tablespoon oleo or butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 to 70 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: butterfingers
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together. Mix sugar and crumbs together and add peanut butter mixture. Melt chips over batter and chill.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Saute onion and celery in hot oil until onion becomes translucent (5 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: hot salad dressing
directions: Combine vinegar and water and heat until it comes to a boil. Combine eggs, sugar, salt and pepper; stir into heated vinegar and water, then cool.
Pour over hard-boiled eggs and lettuce or any other salad.

title: peanut butter cookies(soft!)
directions: Mix all ingredients and add flour.
Roll in 1-inch balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine all, except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Roll in balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cherry cream delight
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy, then add cream of tartar and sugar and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold in saltines and nuts.
Butter oblong dish or pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tan in color, then cool.
Refrigerate if necessary.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots and boil in salty water until tender; cool. Alternate layers of carrots.
Cut up pepper and onion slices (cut thin).
Make marinade, heating until well blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops.
Drain off fat.
Add 1 cup water, celery and soup mix.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Combine flour and parsley with water and thicken pan juices.
Add Pet milk and drained mushrooms.
Cook until thick and bubbly.

title: essie's cobbler
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift flour together with baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan (10 x 5 x 3-inch) or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon drained fruit over batter. Combine 1/4 to 1/2 cup of sugar and fruit juice; pour over fruit and batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients and bring to a
boil. Add onion and green pepper. Pour over carrots. Marinate overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni, brown ground chuck with onions and bell pepper.
Drain and add tomato juice, ketchup and 57 sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place macaroni and beef in bottom of casserole. Layer the can of mushroom soup, the top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Return chicken to broth; add salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Mix 2 cups flour with 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Add strips of dough to mixture.
Cook until dough puffs slightly, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix and simmer.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup of batter into heated and lightly greased griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn; cook until golden.
Keep pancakes warm.
Serve with warm syrup or honey.

title: five bean soup
directions: Combine beans; divide into 4 equal batches, about 3 3/4 cups each.

title: rabbit salad
directions: Put lettuce leaf on plate.
Put pear half on lettuce leaf.
Use almonds for ears, raisins for eyes and cherry for nose.
Place the cottage cheese or marshmallow for tail.
That's all there is to it!

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
One-half cup nuts are optional.
Roll in round balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash with bottom of sugared glass slightly.
Makes approximately 30 cookies, depending on size.
Bake at 325° until done (do not brown), 15 to 20 minutes or less.
Frost when cool with powdered sugar icing.

title: veal chops with vinegar glaze
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper to taste on both sides. Brown in skillet in oil or butter, turning once about 5 minutes per side.
Add garlic, bay leaves and thyme; cook about 3 minutes. Pour the vinegar around the chops and turn heat to high.
Add the broth.
Reduce heat; cover closely and simmer about 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sausage wheel
directions: Drain apples. Brown sausage in 1 tablespoon oil in 10-inch ovenproof skillet. Arrange sausages spoke fashion around 1 apple ring.
Mix batter ingredients until just moistened.
Drop half of the batter between sausages and over center apple ring.
Arrange remaining apple rings over batter.
Carefully spread with reserved batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Cut into wedges.
Serve with hot maple syrup.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir; chill until partially set.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill in oiled pan until set.

title: swiss cube steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Batter in flour.
Country-fry steak until done.
Drain grease.
Pour tomato sauce over steak.
Add onions and peppers.
Cover and let simmer about 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, oats and salt in bowl.
Add melted butter, vanilla and soda mixed in 1/4 cup hot water.
Work with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Heat enough salted water to cover potatoes (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain; slip off skins.
Cut potatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, water and salt in 8-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Add sweet potato slices; stir gently until glazed and heated through.

title: roasted chicken breasts with chilies
directions: Slice chicken into narrow strips.
Season with salt.
Grill to desired degree of doneness on grill.
Saute jalapeno peppers, tomato and onion in oil in skillet; drain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries.
Heat juice and water with cornstarch until thick and clear.
Stir in jello.
Mix well.
Stir in strawberries and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped topping before serving.
This is especially attractive with a spoon of whipped topping in center of pie slice with a fresh unstemmed strawberry stuck in center of the topping.

title: 5 egg pound cake
directions: Flour and grease tube cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake for 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: scalloped chicken supreme
directions: Pour chicken stock over boiled rice.
Place in alternate layers in greased 11 x 7-inch dish the cooked rice, cut up chicken and chicken gravy.
Sprinkle slivered almonds, pimiento and mushrooms over each layer.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or Wheaties.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
(I don't always use pimentos; I usually use more mushrooms and almonds.)

title: frosted chocolate covered bananas
directions: Peel 3 bananas.
Cut each in half.
Push a popsicle stick in halfway.
Wrap in foil and freeze overnight.
Melt in a double boiler chocolate chips and shortening; stir constantly.
Dip bananas in melted chocolate.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Yum!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour 1 can of beans in casserole dish; sprinkle with half of onions.
Pour other can of beans over onions.
Mix mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese soup together (may thin this down with a little water).
Pour over all and simmer in 350° oven until bubbly hot. Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining onions on top and bake until golden brown.
Makes large casserole.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips, add butter and sugar, then eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers and tomatoes; let drain 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Combine all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Cook on top of stove 10 minutes, stirring often.
If desired, a double boiler can be used for cooking to avoid sticking.
Remove from stove and add mayonnaise.
Put in jars and seal; process 5 or 10 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Serve with mini bagels or other snack chips.

title: microwave turkey tetrazzini
directions: Put drained spaghetti in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable pan.
In 2-quart casserole, microwave butter, mushrooms, onion and lemon juice on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and paprika until smooth.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir well.
Add broth; microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add half and half and turkey; blend well.
Pour over spaghetti in pan; sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes, turning twice.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Add enough flour until this comes together and add pinch of baking powder.
You may roll out or drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth.
Do not cover pot.

title: turkey and mushroom burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Divide mixture into 4 or 6 portions and shape into patties.
Place burgers on greased grill (6 inches from heat), medium high on gas fire grill. Cook 6 to 8 minutes per side or until meat is no longer pink inside.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and chill until slightly congealed.
Mix cream cheese, 3 tablespoons pineapple juice, nuts and salt.
Add this to the slightly congealed jello; mix well.
Return to the refrigerator and let chill until firm.

title: ants on a log(easy recipes for kids)
directions: Spread peanut butter or pimento cheese onto celery stick. Place ants (raisins) on top of spread.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water;	set aside.
Stir flour, sugar and
baking soda together.	Cut in shortening until the size
of peas.
Mix buttermilk with yeast water; add to flour mixture. Stir
with	a
fork until moistened.
May be covered and refrigerated overnight to be shaped and baked later.
Turn out onto
floured
surface.
Knead
until smooth and elastic. Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits out with a 2-inch cutter.
Place close together on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake
in
preheated
oven
for 15 to 20 minutes. Brush
with melted
butter or margarine.
Makes 24 to 30 biscuits.

title: coconut pies (4)
directions: Whip all ingredients with big spoon.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: hill's low salt diet(for dogs with heart problems)
directions: Cook beef in skillet, stirring until
lightly
browned. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Keep covered
in
the refrigerator.
Yields 1 pound.

title: venison country fry
directions: Soak cubed venison in buttermilk; coat with flour.
Cook quickly in hot oil, turning several times, adding salt and pepper to steaks.
Remove steaks when well done.
Add soup to drippings and 1 can water.
Stir well and simmer for several minutes.
Serve venison with rice or gravy.

title: sausage casserole 2
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Chop sausage.
Add soup, onion, milk, cheese and mushrooms.
Stir together well and simmer for approximately 10 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni noodles to the mixture and stir.
Simmer for approximately 15 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Stir in Cool Whip.
In large bowl, mix apples, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Toss with cooled dressing and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: supreme dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Form crust, bottom and sides.

title: shocking dip
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl; add gelatin and milk.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended and smooth.
Chill until serving time.
Take out about 15 minutes prior to serving with fruit. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: k.i.s.s. roast(keeping it simple and succulent)
directions: Insert slivered garlic into roast.
In frypan, brown roast in butter.
Mix together soy sauce, ginger, sherry, paprika, salt and water.
Pour over roast.
Arrange celery in large pot or Dutch oven; place roast on top.
Cover tightly.
Roast at 250° for 3 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.
Remove roast from pan; place on warm serving dish.
Discard celery.

title: stuffed beef rolls
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.

Cut into 8 serving pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Brush lightly with mustard. Top each piece with some of the chopped bacon, onion and thin slices of pickle. Roll firmly and fasten with thin white cord or small wooden picks.
Melt butter or other fat in a heavy skillet. Dredge rolls with flour and brown on all sides over moderate heat.

Add bouillon and cooking wine. Cover and simmer gently until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Transfer to a warm serving dish. Combine remaining 1 tablespoon of butter with flour and blend. Add to pan drippings; cook and stir until thickened. If mixture is too thick, thin to the desired consistency with a little water. Serve with mashed potatoes, green beans and leaf lettuce salad.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Thoroughly mash bananas and add to the creamed mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together 3 times the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Add banana mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add pecans, if desired.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Mix margarine and eggs together.
Add cake mix, nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan and line with wax paper.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn on rack to cool.

title: baked fish
directions: Cut fish into serving portions.
Place in a single layer in well greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, onions and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over fish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: lime cream salad
directions: Make Jell-O as usual.
In separate bowl, cream the cream cheese.
Add a little Jell-O to the cheese and mix with mixer until blended smoothly.
Blend in remaining Jell-O.
Add pineapple and nuts.
This must be stirred several times while chilling until it gets fairly thick.
May be used as a dessert or salad.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and place in greased 4-quart casserole dish. Bake until warm at 375° to 400° about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
(Do not add water to chicken soup.)

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.

title: shrimp appetizer platter
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread over 12-inch pizza pan or on serving plate.
Cover with seafood sauce. Layer on shrimp, cheese, pepper, green onions and tomato.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all and roll into balls.
Roll balls in coconut to coat.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix and set overnight.
Make out into balls and freeze.
(Must freeze.)
Do not thaw.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Use as a finger food for brunch, party, etc.

title: wowie chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan (ungreased).
Enjoy.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together and pat into 9x13 inch pan.
Melt 1 large package chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Let cool and firm and then cut into squares.

title: garden vegetable platter
directions: Bring to boil spinach, parsley, water, onions and tarragon in small saucepan.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 1 minute.
Drain. Place spinach mixture and all remaining ingredients in blender or food processor container; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Cover. Refrigerate.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Cover and chill.

title: marvelous fruit mix-up(from:  redbook magazine)
directions: In a large bowl, stir 1/2 cup boiling water into gelatin to dissolve completely.
Add ice cubes, stirring constantly 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture slightly thickens.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Stir sour cream into gelatin until blended.
Set aside 1/2 cup pineapple, 1/4 cup oranges and 1 tablespoon walnuts for garnish; stir remaining fruit and nuts into gelatin mixture along with all the marshmallows.
Pour into 8-inch square pan; top with reserved fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Makes 8 servings:
198 calories per serving.

title: winter beef simmer
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In Dutch oven combine chopped onions, bacon and roast.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until meats are browned (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover.
Continue baking, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Sprinkle pepper and Mrs. Dash seasoning on chicken in a baking dish. Empty can of soup into dish and wash can with 1/2 cup water and add to chicken. Stir gently to coat chicken and spread soup evenly over it. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green beans
directions: In pan, put green beans, 2 cans of fresh water and onion.
Cut bacon into tiny pieces and add to beans.
(Can add diced ham instead, if desired.)
Cook on medium to low heat until bacon is done.
Add more water, if needed.
Put in serving dish and add 2 to 3 pats of butter for flavor.

title: german chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, 1 egg (beaten) and pecans.
Press into bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: pineapple rice pudding
directions: Beat yolks of eggs well, then mix with rice.
Add sugar, milk and pineapple.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites; pour into a buttered pan or glass ovenware.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Stir together and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Brownies are very moist and delicious.

title: poached fish with lemon and dill
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine broth, wine, dill and lemon.
Over medium-high heat, heat to boiling.
Arrange fish in broth mixture. Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Discard poaching liquid. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pans.
In large bowl, with fork, mix flour with the first 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Cook macaroni.
Mix pizza sauce with hamburger and macaroni.
Put this mixture on bottom of a roaster; top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: flat dumplings or noodles
directions: Add water and eggs together.
Beat until mixed well.
Add flour and stir until stiff.
Roll out on floured area.
Cut into squares or noodles and let dry.
Add to chicken broth, beef broth or soup broth.
Cook until done.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Coat a skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook and stir onion over medium heat until transparent, approximately 5 minutes. Add spinach; cook until thoroughly heated, 1 to 2 minutes.
Reduce heat; add cream cheese.
Stir until melted smooth.
Stir in sour cream, Parmesan cheese and artichoke hearts.
Remove from heat. Season with peppers and salt.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Top with Jack cheese and heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: easy chile
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add onion and garlic and cook until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer a couple of hours.

title: savory stuffed squash
directions: Wash and cut squash lengthwise.
Scoop out center to 1/4-inch of edge.
Place in salted boiling water for about 5 minutes; remove and drain.
Fry sausage and drain well.
Mix stuffing according to directions.
Let sit and then mix sausage with dressing.
Spoon mixture into squash.
Place in baking pan.
Place enough water in pan to cover bottom.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Beat well.
Let raise; cut out with cutter.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown, turning once.
Very good and easy!

title: special chocolate icing
directions: Combine corn syrup, water and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil quickly, stirring until butter is melted.
Remove from heat; add chocolate.
Stir until completely melted.
Cool to room temperature before pouring over cake, petit fours or desired dessert to glaze; chill until set.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot meatballs
directions: Mix in bowl beets, carrots, onion, egg, milk, salt and pepper. Shape in 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Heat oil in large skillet and brown meatballs. Add gravy. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until meatballs are done. If desired, serve over noodles or rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: potato and fish chowder
directions: Cook fish, potatoes and carrots in the water for about 15 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, brown sugar and seasoning.
Add beef, let stand 20 minutes to marinate.
Stir-fry beef in hot oil in skillet until browned.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Mix broth and cornstarch, add to skillet.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Press ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Top with chocolate icing and keep refrigerated.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to make 1 1/3 cups; bring to a boil.
Place Jell-O in a bowl.
Add boiling liquid and stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.
In a mixing bowl, whip cream; gradually add in the sugar.
Fold in the Jell-O mixture. Stir in the crushed pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well. Pour into a 1 1/2 quart serving bowl.
Chill at least overnight. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press dough into ungreased cookie sheet (both packages).
Be sure that it's pressed together (like a pizza crust).
Cook 5 to 6 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Mix Hidden Valley dip mix, mayo and cream cheese together.
Spread over top of cooled crust.
Sprinkle with diced veggies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine wafer crumbs with butter and brown sugar.
Reserve 1 cup; spread remaining mixture in 9 x 14-inch dish.
Blend vanilla with whipped cream; spread over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Cover with pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Yields 8 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
In large bowl mix cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat on low speed until moistened.
Then beat for 2 minutes on high.
Spoon batter evenly over coconut and pecans.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into two 7 1/2 x 4-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt butter; add flour and salt.
Stir until smooth paste. Combine chicken stock and evaporated milk.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
In casserole dish, make a bottom layer of broccoli and top layer of chicken.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: baked green beans
directions: Wash gren beans.
Trim ends and remove strings.
Place beans in a

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips.

title: tuna and noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except for bagel.
Mix well.
Spray medium size casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle top with fat-free cheese and chopped bagel.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve.
Yields 4 servings. Per serving has 1 gram fat and 220 calories.

title: pan coating
directions: Beat ingredients together until creamy and fluffy with mixer. Store in plastic container and use to grease cake and cookie pans.
Also good on pizza pans, sprinkled with a little corn meal.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine beaten egg yolks, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients, beating until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter on hot waffle iron and bake until brown.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle cut up pieces of chicken well with Season-All (both sides).
Place in baking dish, skin side up.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice and pour over chicken pieces in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 225° for 2 hours or 375° to 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn once to brown on both sides.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Top with crushed cheese bits.
Cook in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Chill milk in freezer until icy.
Whip until it holds peaks. Add sugar; whip well.
Add Kool-Aid.
Chill crust slightly.
Pour pie mix into crust and freeze.
Do not use pre-sweetened Kool-Aid!

title: pimento potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Reserve potato water.
In saucepan, melt butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup reserved potato water and milk.
Cook until almost as thick as mashed potatoes, stirring constantly.
Add Cheddar cheese, pimentos and onions. Stir well.
Pour over drained potatoes and stir.
Cube 4 cups bread crumbs and pour first melted butter over them.
Arrange on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° until crisp.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Set aside.
In skillet, combine remaining ingredients. Heat to boil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.

title: bonanza bread
directions: Combine flour mixture of your choice with salt, soda, baking powder, dry milk, wheat germ, sugar, nuts and raisins in a large bowl, then blend thoroughly.
Whirl eggs in container of electric blender until foamy.
Add oil, molasses, orange juice and bananas, whirling after each addition.
Add apricots; whirl just to chop coarsely.
Pour mixture into bowl with dry ingredients.
Stir just until all flour is moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans, 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour until center is firm when touched lightly with fingertip.
Cool slightly on pan or wire rack, then remove from pan and cool completely. When cool, wrap tightly and store overnight to mellow flavors.
Can be baked in muffin pans at 350° for 20 minutes.
Recipe makes 3 dozen or 36 muffins.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix and spread in casserole dish:
apples, cranberries and sugar.
Mix and spread over fruit:
oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, margarine and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add zucchini, chopped nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Frost with icing.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large shallow baking dish, microwave butter on High until melted, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on High until boils, about 3 minutes, stirring once. Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes without stirring.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Stir in popped popcorn.
Microwave on 75% for approximately 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes to coat.
Cool 100%.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin-chocolate chip bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, 2 teaspoons cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
In a medium mixing bowl combine eggs, pumpkin, 1 1/2 cups sugar and oil.
Add flour mixture and mix just until moistened.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Spread in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Stir together 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the pineapple over the pie filling.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pineapple.
Put pats of butter over the whole thing by cutting it into squares and placing on cake spacing apart.
Sprinkle the coconut over the cake.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 375°. Remove foil.
Brown top.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate slowly in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients to melted mixture, stirring while bringing to a boil. Then chill.
Warm in microwave or boiling water and use over ice cream.

title: pink parfait sandwich spread
directions: Drain pineapple; drain cherries and chip very fine.
Blend cream cheese, adding cherry juice to soften and color the cheese. Add pineapple, nuts and cherries.
If more liquid is needed, use pineapple juice.
Makes 100 party sandwiches.
Cut with fancy cutters or into tiny squares, strips or triangles.

title: beet and jello salad
directions: Drain beets and reserve juice.
Add enough water to beet juice to make 1 cup liquid.
In medium saucepan, combine beet juice mixture with vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
Stir in dry gelatin until completely dissolved. Allow mixture to cool in saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add beets and pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate overnight, until set.

title: noodles kugel
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Boil noodles, leave slightly underdone.
Let stand in cold water until needed.
Pare and slice thinly the apples; add cinnamon, nutmeg, orange juice, lemon peel and sugar.
Mix and let stand.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put ingredients in layers, starting with noodles and ending with apples.
Sprinkle raisins on each layer.
Pour remaining juice over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
No raisins on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve and chill until syrupy the jello and boiling water. Add the drained crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Chill until set.
Spread the mixture of creamed cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla over top.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Add all ingredients including juice and stir.
Put in serving dish.
Add nuts on top.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all but the carrots, green pepper and onion in a saucepan. Heat until all ingredients are well mixed and sugar is dissolved. Pour sauce (while still hot) over carrots, onion and green peppers.
Refrigerate.

title: bavarian apple cheese cake
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar, margarine or butter, shortening and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla until combined.
Blend in flour and salt until crumbly.
Pat on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Place apple slices in shallow baking pan; cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes with ham
directions: Saute onion lightly in margarine; blend well the soup, milk and Velveeta.
Stir in onion.
Add potatoes and ham; mix gently.
No added salt needed.
Bake in covered dish at 325° for 45 minutes. Be sure entire mixture bubbles.
May add additional milk if needed while baking.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and milk; beat again.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Put in cold oven and turn oven on 350°. Bake until set.
You may add 1 cup coconut, if you want coconut custard.
Takes about 45 minutes or longer to bake.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Make half slice marks down across hot dogs.
Fry onion in oil or butter.
Place hot dogs on top.
Mix together ketchup, vinegar, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar and dry mustard.
Pour over hot dogs and simmer on stove until hot dogs are cooked.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in salt and flour; mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in sugar while warm, then cool and roll in sugar again. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: easy brownie bar
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add flour and chopped nuts. Add the Hershey's syrup; mix well.
Pour into a 12 x 17-inch greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Remove from stove and add the box of chocolate cake mix.
Stir until cake mix is moistened.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
Crumble into pieces and place in punch bowl.
Pour pineapple, with part of the juice reserved, over the cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding mix and add the bananas. Pour over the cake mixture, then on top of pudding, pour the cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cover and chill.
Add nuts, coconut and cherries on top before serving.

title: stuffed cabbage roll
directions: Precook rice; strain.

Using a large bowl, mix all the ingredients except the margarine, tomato soup and cabbage. Prepare cabbage by cutting around the heart to loosen the leaves. Heat the cabbage in a pot with about three inches of water to loosen leaves.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until brown and drain.
Set aside. Separate dough in 8 triangles; point toward center in greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust.
Press perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well. Store in tightly covered jar in the refrigerator.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: white christmas candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Melt chocolate in microwave or in a double boiler, being careful not to overheat.
Pour over cereal mixture and blend thoroughly. Spread thin on waxed paper.
When cool, break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes 1 gallon of candy treats.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together and shake well each time before using.
Recipe makes almost a quart and will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.
